159 static void assign( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string_view name,
160  std::map<gun_mode_id, gun_modifier_data> &mods )
161 {
162  if( !jo.has_array( name ) ) {
163  return;
164  }
165  mods.clear();
166  for( JsonArray curr : jo.get_array( name ) ) {
167  translation text;
168  curr.read( 1, text );
169  mods.emplace( gun_mode_id( curr.get_string( 0 ) ), gun_modifier_data( text,
170  curr.get_int( 2 ), curr.size() >= 4 ? curr.get_tags( 3 ) : std::set<std::string>() ) );
171  }
172 }
173 
174 static bool assign_coverage_from_json( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &key,
175  body_part_set &parts )
176 {
177  auto parse = [&parts]( const std::string & val ) {
178  parts.set( bodypart_str_id( val ) );
179  };
180 
181  if( jo.has_array( key ) ) {
182  for( const std::string line : jo.get_array( key ) ) {
183  parse( line );
184  }
185  return true;
186 
187  } else if( jo.has_string( key ) ) {
188  parse( jo.get_string( key ) );
189  return true;
190 
191  } else {
192  return false;
193  }
194 }
195 
196 static bool assign_coverage_from_json( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &key,
197  std::optional<body_part_set> &parts )
198 {
199  body_part_set temp;
200  if( assign_coverage_from_json( jo, key, temp ) ) {
201  parts = temp;
202  return true;
203  }
204 
205  return false;
206 }

208 static bool is_physical( const itype &type )
209 {
210  return !type.has_flag( flag_AURA ) &&
211  !type.has_flag( flag_CORPSE ) &&
212  !type.has_flag( flag_IRREMOVABLE ) &&
213  !type.has_flag( flag_NO_DROP ) &&
214  !type.has_flag( flag_NO_UNWIELD ) &&
215  !type.has_flag( flag_PERSONAL ) &&
216  !type.has_flag( flag_PSEUDO ) &&
217  !type.has_flag( flag_ZERO_WEIGHT );
218 }

220 void Item_factory::finalize_pre( itype &obj )
221 {
222  // Add relic data by ID we defered
223  if( obj.relic_data ) {
224  obj.relic_data->finalize();
225  }
226 
227  if( obj.count_by_charges() ) {
228  obj.item_tags.insert( flag_NO_REPAIR );
229  }
230 
231  finalize_damage_map( obj.melee );
232  if( !obj.melee_proportional.empty() ) {
233  finalize_damage_map( obj.melee_proportional, false, 1.f );
234  for( std::pair<const damage_type_id, float> &dt : obj.melee ) {
235  const auto iter = obj.melee_proportional.find( dt.first );
236  if( iter != obj.melee_proportional.end() ) {
237  dt.second *= iter->second;
238  // For maintaining legacy behaviour (when melee damage used ints)
239  dt.second = std::floor( dt.second );
240  }
241  }
242  }
243  if( !obj.melee_relative.empty() ) {
244  finalize_damage_map( obj.melee_relative, false, 0.f );
245  for( std::pair<const damage_type_id, float> &dt : obj.melee ) {
246  const auto iter = obj.melee_relative.find( dt.first );
247  if( iter != obj.melee_relative.end() ) {
248  dt.second += iter->second;
249  // For maintaining legacy behaviour (when melee damage used ints)
250  dt.second = std::floor( dt.second );
251  }
252  }
253  }
254 
255  if( obj.has_flag( flag_STAB ) ) {
256  debugmsg( "The \"STAB\" flag used on %s is obsolete, add a \"stab\" value in the \"melee_damage\" object instead.",
257  obj.id.c_str() );
258  }
259 
260  // add usage methods (with default values) based upon qualities
261  // if a method was already set the specific values remain unchanged
262  for( const auto &q : obj.qualities ) {
263  for( const auto &u : q.first.obj().usages ) {
264  if( q.second >= u.first ) {
265  emplace_usage( obj.use_methods, u.second );
266  // As far as I know all the actions provided by quality level do not consume ammo
267  // So it is safe to set all to 0
268  // To do: read the json file of this item again and get for each quality a scale number
269  obj.ammo_scale.emplace( u.second, 0 );
270  }
271  }
272  }
273  for( const auto &q : obj.charged_qualities ) {
274  for( const auto &u : q.first.obj().usages ) {
275  if( q.second >= u.first ) {
276  emplace_usage( obj.use_methods, u.second );
277  // I do not know how to get the ammo scale, so hopefully it naturally comes with the item's scale?
278  }
279  }
280  }
281 
282  if( obj.mod ) {
283  std::string func = obj.gunmod ? "GUNMOD_ATTACH" : "TOOLMOD_ATTACH";
284  emplace_usage( obj.use_methods, func );
285  obj.ammo_scale.emplace( func, 0 );
286  } else if( obj.gun ) {
287  const std::string func = "detach_gunmods";
288  emplace_usage( obj.use_methods, func );
289  obj.ammo_scale.emplace( func, 0 );
290  const std::string func2 = "modify_gunmods";
291  emplace_usage( obj.use_methods, func2 );
292  obj.ammo_scale.emplace( func2, 0 );
293  }
294 
295  if( get_option<bool>( "NO_FAULTS" ) ) {
296  obj.faults.clear();
297  }
298 
299  // If no category was forced via JSON automatically calculate one now
300  if( !obj.category_force.is_valid() || obj.category_force.is_empty() ) {
301  obj.category_force = calc_category( obj );
302  }
303 
304  // use pre-Cataclysm price as default if post-cataclysm price unspecified
305  if( obj.price_post < 0_cent ) {
306  obj.price_post = obj.price;
307  }
308  // use base volume if integral volume unspecified
309  if( obj.integral_volume < 0_ml ) {
310  obj.integral_volume = obj.volume;
311  }
312  // use base weight if integral weight unspecified
313  if( obj.integral_weight < 0_gram ) {
314  obj.integral_weight = obj.weight;
315  }
316  // for ammo and comestibles stack size defaults to count of initial charges
317  // Set max stack size to 200 to prevent integer overflow
318  if( obj.count_by_charges() ) {
319  if( obj.stack_size == 0 ) {
320  obj.stack_size = obj.charges_default();
321  } else if( obj.stack_size > 200 ) {
322  debugmsg( obj.id.str() + " stack size is too large, reducing to 200" );
323  obj.stack_size = 200;
324  }
325  }
326 
327  // Items always should have some volume.
328  // TODO: handle possible exception software?
329  if( obj.volume <= 0_ml ) {
330  if( is_physical( obj ) ) {
331  debugmsg( "item %s has zero volume (if zero volume is intentional "
332  "you can suppress this error with the ZERO_WEIGHT "
333  "flag)\n", obj.id.str() );
334  }
335  obj.volume = units::from_milliliter( 1 );
336  }
337 
338  // set light_emission based on LIGHT_[X] flag
339  for( const auto &f : obj.item_tags ) {
340  if( string_starts_with( f.str(), "LIGHT_" ) ) {
341  ret_val<int> ll = try_parse_integer<int>( f.str().substr( 6 ), false );
342  if( ll.success() ) {
343  if( ll.value() > 0 ) {
344  obj.light_emission = ll.value();
345  } else {
346  debugmsg( "item %s specifies light emission of zero, which is redundant",
347  obj.id.str() );
348  }
349  } else {
350  debugmsg( "error parsing integer light emission suffic for item %s: %s",
351  obj.id.str(), ll.str() );
352  }
353  }
354  }
355  // remove LIGHT_[X] flags
356  erase_if( obj.item_tags, []( const flag_id & f ) {
357  return string_starts_with( f.str(), "LIGHT_" );
358  } );
359 
360  // Finalize vitamins in food
361  if( obj.comestible ) {
362  obj.comestible->default_nutrition.finalize_vitamins();
363 
364  bool is_not_boring = false;
365  float specific_heat_solid = 0.0f;
366  float specific_heat_liquid = 0.0f;
367  float latent_heat = 0.0f;
368  int mat_total = 0;
369 
370  auto add_spi = [&is_not_boring, &specific_heat_solid, &specific_heat_liquid, &latent_heat,
371  &mat_total]( const material_id & m, int portion ) {
372  specific_heat_solid += m->specific_heat_solid() * portion;
373  specific_heat_liquid += m->specific_heat_liquid() * portion;
374  latent_heat += m->latent_heat() * portion;
375  mat_total += portion;
376  is_not_boring = is_not_boring || m == material_junk;
377  };
378 
379  for( const std::pair <const material_id, int> &pair : obj.comestible->materials ) {
380  add_spi( pair.first, pair.second );
381  }
382 
383  // Average based on number of materials.
384  obj.comestible->specific_heat_liquid = specific_heat_liquid / mat_total;
385  obj.comestible->specific_heat_solid = specific_heat_solid / mat_total;
386  obj.comestible->latent_heat = latent_heat / mat_total;
387 
388  // Junk food never gets old by default, but this can still be overridden.
389  if( obj.comestible->monotony_penalty == -1 ) {
390  obj.comestible->monotony_penalty = is_not_boring ? 0 : 2;
391  }
392  }
393 
394  // for ammo not specifying loudness derive value from other properties
395  if( obj.ammo ) {
396  if( obj.ammo->loudness < 0 ) {
397  obj.ammo->loudness = obj.ammo->range * 2;
398  for( const damage_unit &du : obj.ammo->damage ) {
399  obj.ammo->loudness += ( du.amount + du.res_pen ) * 2;
400  }
401  }
402 
403  const auto &mats = obj.materials;
404  if( mats.find( material_hydrocarbons ) == mats.end() &&
405  mats.find( material_oil ) == mats.end() ) {
406  const auto &ammo_effects = obj.ammo->ammo_effects;
407  obj.ammo->cookoff = ammo_effects.count( "INCENDIARY" ) > 0 ||
408  ammo_effects.count( "COOKOFF" ) > 0;
409  static const std::set<std::string> special_cookoff_tags = {{
410  "SPECIAL_COOKOFF"
411  }
412  };
413  obj.ammo->special_cookoff = std::any_of( ammo_effects.begin(), ammo_effects.end(),
414  []( const std::string & s ) {
415  return special_cookoff_tags.count( s ) > 0;
416  } );
417  } else {
418  obj.ammo->cookoff = false;
419  obj.ammo->special_cookoff = false;
420  }
421  // Special casing for shot, since the damage per pellet can be tiny.
422  // Instead of handling fractional damage values, we scale the effective number
423  // of projectiles based on the damage so that they end up at 1.
424  if( obj.ammo->count > 1 && obj.ammo->shot_damage.total_damage() < 1.0f ) {
425  // Patch to fixup shot without shot_damage until I get all the definitions consistent.
426  if( obj.ammo->shot_damage.damage_units.empty() ) {
427  obj.ammo->shot_damage.damage_units.emplace_back( damage_bullet, 0.1f );
428  }
429  obj.ammo->count = obj.ammo->count * obj.ammo->shot_damage.total_damage();
430  obj.ammo->shot_damage.damage_units.front().amount = 1.0f;
431  }
432  }
433 
434  // Helper for ammo migration in following sections
435  auto migrate_ammo_set = [this]( std::set<ammotype> &ammoset ) {
436  for( auto ammo_type_it = ammoset.begin(); ammo_type_it != ammoset.end(); ) {
437  const itype_id default_ammo_type = ammo_type_it->obj().default_ammotype();
438  auto maybe_migrated = migrated_ammo.find( default_ammo_type );
439  if( maybe_migrated != migrated_ammo.end() ) {
440  ammo_type_it = ammoset.erase( ammo_type_it );
441  ammoset.insert( maybe_migrated->second );
442  } else {
443  ++ammo_type_it;
444  }
445  }
446  };
447 
448  auto migrate_ammo_map = [this]( std::map<ammotype, int> &ammomap ) {
449  for( auto ammo_type_it = ammomap.begin(); ammo_type_it != ammomap.end(); ) {
450  const itype_id default_ammo_type = ammo_type_it->first.obj().default_ammotype();
451  auto maybe_migrated = migrated_ammo.find( default_ammo_type );
452  if( maybe_migrated != migrated_ammo.end() ) {
453  int capacity = ammo_type_it->second;
454  ammo_type_it = ammomap.erase( ammo_type_it );
455  ammomap.emplace( maybe_migrated->second, capacity );
456  } else {
457  ++ammo_type_it;
458  }
459  }
460  };
461 
462  if( obj.magazine ) {
463  // ensure default_ammo is set
464  if( obj.magazine->default_ammo.is_null() ) {
465  obj.magazine->default_ammo = ammotype( *obj.magazine->type.begin() )->default_ammotype();
466  }
467 
468  // If the magazine has ammo types for which the default ammo has been migrated, we need to
469  // replace those ammo types with that of the migrated ammo
470  migrate_ammo_set( obj.magazine->type );
471 
472  // ensure default_ammo is migrated if need be
473  auto maybe_migrated = migrated_ammo.find( obj.magazine->default_ammo );
474  if( maybe_migrated != migrated_ammo.end() ) {
475  obj.magazine->default_ammo = maybe_migrated->second.obj().default_ammotype();
476  }
477 
478  for( pocket_data &magazine : obj.pockets ) {
479  if( magazine.type != pocket_type::MAGAZINE ) {
480  continue;
481  }
482  migrate_ammo_map( magazine.ammo_restriction );
483  }
484 
485  // list all the ammo types that work
486  for( const ammotype &am : obj.magazine->type ) {
487  auto temp_vec = Item_factory::find( [obj, am]( const itype & e ) {
488  if( !e.ammo || item_is_blacklisted( e.get_id() ) ) {
489  return false;
490  }
491 
492  return e.ammo->type == am;
493  } );
494 
495  for( const itype *val : temp_vec ) {
496  obj.magazine->cached_ammos[am].insert( val->get_id() );
497  }
498  }
499 
500  }
501 
502  // Migrate compatible magazines
503  for( auto kv : obj.magazines ) {
504  for( auto mag_it = kv.second.begin(); mag_it != kv.second.end(); ) {
505  auto maybe_migrated = migrated_magazines.find( *mag_it );
506  if( maybe_migrated != migrated_magazines.end() ) {
507  mag_it = kv.second.erase( mag_it );
508  kv.second.insert( kv.second.begin(), maybe_migrated->second );
509  } else {
510  ++mag_it;
511  }
512  }
513  }
514 
515  // Migrate default magazines
516  for( auto kv : obj.magazine_default ) {
517  auto maybe_migrated = migrated_magazines.find( kv.second );
518  if( maybe_migrated != migrated_magazines.end() ) {
519  kv.second = maybe_migrated->second;
520  }
521  }
522 
523  if( obj.mod ) {
524  // Migrate acceptable ammo and ammo modifiers
525  migrate_ammo_set( obj.mod->acceptable_ammo );
526  migrate_ammo_set( obj.mod->ammo_modifier );
527 
528  for( auto kv = obj.mod->magazine_adaptor.begin(); kv != obj.mod->magazine_adaptor.end(); ) {
529  auto maybe_migrated = migrated_ammo.find( kv->first.obj().default_ammotype() );
530  if( maybe_migrated != migrated_ammo.end() ) {
531  for( const itype_id &compatible_mag : kv->second ) {
532  obj.mod->magazine_adaptor[maybe_migrated->second].insert( compatible_mag );
533  }
534  kv = obj.mod->magazine_adaptor.erase( kv );
535  } else {
536  ++kv;
537  }
538  }
539  }

541  if( obj.gun ) {
542  // If the gun has ammo types for which the default ammo has been migrated, we need to
543  // replace those ammo types with that of the migrated ammo
544  for( auto ammo_type_it = obj.gun->ammo.begin(); ammo_type_it != obj.gun->ammo.end(); ) {
545  auto maybe_migrated = migrated_ammo.find( ammo_type_it->obj().default_ammotype() );
546  if( maybe_migrated != migrated_ammo.end() ) {
547  const ammotype old_ammo = *ammo_type_it;
548  // Remove the old ammotype add the migrated version
549  ammo_type_it = obj.gun->ammo.erase( ammo_type_it );
550  const ammotype &new_ammo = maybe_migrated->second;
551  obj.gun->ammo.insert( obj.gun->ammo.begin(), new_ammo );
552  // Migrate the compatible magazines
553  auto old_mag_it = obj.magazines.find( old_ammo );
554  if( old_mag_it != obj.magazines.end() ) {
555  for( const itype_id &old_mag : old_mag_it->second ) {
556  obj.magazines[new_ammo].insert( old_mag );
557  }
558  obj.magazines.erase( old_ammo );
559  }
560  // And the default magazines for each magazine type
561  auto old_default_mag_it = obj.magazine_default.find( old_ammo );
562  if( old_default_mag_it != obj.magazine_default.end() ) {
563  const itype_id &old_default_mag = old_default_mag_it->second;
564  obj.magazine_default[new_ammo] = old_default_mag;
565  obj.magazine_default.erase( old_ammo );
566  }
567  } else {
568  ++ammo_type_it;
569  }
570  }
571 
572  // generate cached map for [mag type_id] -> [set of compatible guns]
573  for( const pocket_data &pocket : obj.pockets ) {
574  if( pocket.type != pocket_type::MAGAZINE_WELL ) {
575  continue;
576  }
577  for( const itype_id &mag_type_id : pocket.item_id_restriction ) {
578  if( item_is_blacklisted( mag_type_id ) || item_is_blacklisted( obj.id ) ) {
579  continue;
580  }
581  islot_magazine::compatible_guns[mag_type_id].insert( obj.id );
582  }
583  }
584 
585  for( pocket_data &magazine : obj.pockets ) {
586  if( magazine.type != pocket_type::MAGAZINE ) {
587  continue;
588  }
589  migrate_ammo_map( magazine.ammo_restriction );
590  }
591 
592  // TODO: add explicit action field to gun definitions
593  const auto defmode_name = [&]() {
594  if( obj.gun->clip == 1 ) {
595  return to_translation( "manual" ); // break-type actions
596  } else if( obj.gun->skill_used == skill_pistol && obj.has_flag( flag_RELOAD_ONE ) ) {
597  return to_translation( "revolver" );
598  } else {
599  return to_translation( "semi-auto" );
600  }
601  };
602 
603  // if the gun doesn't have a DEFAULT mode then add one now
604  obj.gun->modes.emplace( gun_mode_DEFAULT,
605  gun_modifier_data( defmode_name(), 1, std::set<std::string>() ) );
606 
607  // If a "gun" has a reach attack, give it an additional melee mode.
608  if( obj.has_flag( flag_REACH_ATTACK ) ) {
609  obj.gun->modes.emplace( gun_mode_MELEE,
610  gun_modifier_data( to_translation( "melee" ), 1,
611  { "MELEE" } ) );
612  }
613 
614  if( obj.gun->handling < 0 ) {
615  // TODO: specify in JSON via classes
616  if( obj.gun->skill_used == skill_rifle ||
617  obj.gun->skill_used == skill_smg ||
618  obj.gun->skill_used == skill_shotgun ) {
619  obj.gun->handling = 20;
620  } else {
621  obj.gun->handling = 10;
622  }
623  }
624 
625  // list all the ammo types that work
626  for( const ammotype &am : obj.gun->ammo ) {
627  auto temp_vec = Item_factory::find( [obj, am]( const itype & e ) {
628  if( !e.ammo || item_is_blacklisted( e.get_id() ) ) {
629  return false;
630  }
631 
632  return e.ammo->type == am;
633  } );
634 
635  for( const itype *val : temp_vec ) {
636  obj.gun->cached_ammos[am].insert( val->get_id() );
637  }
638  }
639 
640  }
641 
642  set_allergy_flags( obj );
643  hflesh_to_flesh( obj );
644  npc_implied_flags( obj );
645 
646  if( obj.comestible ) {
647  std::map<vitamin_id, int> vitamins = obj.comestible->default_nutrition.vitamins();
648  if( get_option<bool>( "NO_VITAMINS" ) ) {
649  for( auto &vit : vitamins ) {
650  if( vit.first->type() == vitamin_type::VITAMIN ) {
651  obj.comestible->default_nutrition.set_vitamin( vit.first, 0 );
652  }
653  }
654  } else if( vitamins.empty() && obj.comestible->healthy >= 0 ) {
655  // Default vitamins of healthy comestibles to their edible base materials if none explicitly specified.
656  int healthy = std::max( obj.comestible->healthy, 1 ) * 10;
657  auto mat = obj.materials;
658 
659  // TODO: migrate inedible comestibles to appropriate alternative types.
660  for( auto m = mat.begin(); m != mat.end(); ) {
661  if( !m->first->edible() ) {
662  m = mat.erase( m );
663  } else {
664  m++;
665  }
666  }
667 
668  // For comestibles composed of multiple edible materials we calculate the average.
669  for( const auto &v : vitamin::all() ) {
670  if( !vitamins.count( v.first ) ) {
671  for( const auto &m : mat ) {
672  double amount = m.first->vitamin( v.first ) * healthy / mat.size();
673  obj.comestible->default_nutrition.add_vitamin( v.first, std::ceil( amount ) );
674  }
675  }
676  }
677  }
678  }
679 
680  // recurse into subtypes, adding self as substitution for all items in the subtypes chain
681  for( itype_id it = obj.id; it->tool && it->tool->subtype.is_valid(); it = it->tool->subtype ) {
682  tool_subtypes[ it->tool->subtype ].insert( obj.id );
683  }
684 
685  for( auto &e : obj.use_methods ) {
686  e.second.get_actor_ptr()->finalize( obj.id );
687  }
688 
689  if( obj.drop_action.get_actor_ptr() != nullptr ) {
690  obj.drop_action.get_actor_ptr()->finalize( obj.id );
691  }
692 
693  if( obj.can_use( "MA_MANUAL" ) && obj.book && obj.book->martial_art.is_null() &&
694  string_starts_with( obj.get_id().str(), "manual_" ) ) {
695  // HACK: Legacy martial arts books rely on a hack whereby the name of the
696  // martial art is derived from the item id
697  obj.book->martial_art = matype_id( "style_" + obj.get_id().str().substr( 7 ) );
698  }
699 
700  if( obj.can_use( "link_up" ) ) {
701  obj.ammo_scale.emplace( "link_up", 0 );
702  }
703 
704  if( obj.longest_side == -1_mm ) {
705  units::volume effective_volume = obj.count_by_charges() &&
706  obj.stack_size > 0 ? ( obj.volume / obj.stack_size ) : obj.volume;
707  obj.longest_side = units::default_length_from_volume<int>( effective_volume );
708  }
709 }
710 
711 void Item_factory::register_cached_uses( const itype &obj )
712 {
713  for( const auto &e : obj.use_methods ) {
714  // can this item function as a repair tool?
715  if( repair_actions.count( e.first ) ) {
716  repair_tools.insert( obj.id );
717  }
718 
719  // can this item be used to repair complex firearms?
720  if( e.first == "GUN_REPAIR" ) {
721  gun_tools.insert( obj.id );
722  }
723  }
724 }
725 
726 void Item_factory::finalize_post( itype &obj )
727 {
728  erase_if( obj.item_tags, [&]( const flag_id & f ) {
729  if( !f.is_valid() ) {
730  debugmsg( "itype '%s' uses undefined flag '%s'. Please add corresponding 'json_flag' entry to json.",
731  obj.id.str(), f.str() );
732  return true;
733  }
734  return false;
735  } );
736 
737  if( obj.gun && !obj.gunmod && !obj.has_flag( flag_PRIMITIVE_RANGED_WEAPON ) ) {
738  const quality_id qual_gun_skill( to_upper_case( obj.gun->skill_used.str() ) );
739 
740  obj.qualities[qual_GUN] = std::max( obj.qualities[qual_GUN], 1 );
741  if( qual_gun_skill.is_valid() ) {
742  obj.qualities[qual_gun_skill] = std::max( obj.qualities[qual_gun_skill], 1 );
743  }
744  }
745 
746  // handle complex firearms as a special case
747  if( obj.gun && !obj.has_flag( flag_PRIMITIVE_RANGED_WEAPON ) ) {
748  std::copy( gun_tools.begin(), gun_tools.end(), std::inserter( obj.repair, obj.repair.begin() ) );
749  return;
750  }
751 
752  if( obj.armor ) {
753  finalize_post_armor( obj );
754  }
755 
756  // if we haven't set what the item can be repaired with calculate it now
757  if( obj.repairs_with.empty() ) {
758  for( const auto &mats : obj.materials ) {
759  obj.repairs_with.insert( mats.first );
760  }
761  }
762 
763  // for each item iterate through potential repair tools
764  for( const auto &tool : repair_tools ) {
765 
766  // check if item can be repaired with any of the actions?
767  for( const auto &act : repair_actions ) {
768  const use_function *func = m_templates[tool].get_use( act );
769  if( func == nullptr ) {
770  continue;
771  }
772 
773  // tool has a possible repair action, check if the materials are compatible
774  const auto &opts = dynamic_cast<const repair_item_actor *>( func->get_actor_ptr() )->materials;
775  if( std::any_of( obj.repairs_with.begin(),
776  obj.repairs_with.end(), [&opts]( const material_id & m ) {
777  return opts.count( m ) > 0;
778  } ) ) {
779  obj.repair.insert( tool );
780  }
781  }
782  }
783 
784  if( obj.has_flag( json_flag_NO_UNLOAD ) ) {
785  for( pocket_data &pocket : obj.pockets ) {
786  pocket._no_unload = true;
787  }
788  }
789 
790  if( obj.has_flag( json_flag_NO_RELOAD ) ) {
791  for( pocket_data &pocket : obj.pockets ) {
792  pocket._no_reload = true;
793  }
794  }
795 
796  // go through each pocket and assign the name as a fallback definition
797  for( pocket_data &pocket : obj.pockets ) {
798  pocket.name = obj.name;
799  }
800 
801  if( obj.comestible ) {
802  for( const std::pair<const diseasetype_id, int> &elem : obj.comestible->contamination ) {
803  const diseasetype_id dtype = elem.first;
804  if( !dtype.is_valid() ) {
805  debugmsg( "contamination in %s contains invalid diseasetype_id %s.",
806  obj.id.str(), dtype.str() );
807  }
808  }
809  }
810 }
811 
812 void Item_factory::finalize_post_armor( itype &obj )
813 {
814  // Tally up all the hard-defined similar BPs
815  for( armor_portion_data &data : obj.armor->sub_data ) {
816  body_part_set similar_bp;
817  if( data.covers.has_value() ) {
818  for( const bodypart_str_id &bp : data.covers.value() ) {
819  for( const bodypart_str_id &similar : bp->similar_bodyparts ) {
820  similar_bp.set( similar );
821  }
822  }
823  }
824  data.covers->unify_set( similar_bp );
825  }
826 
827  // Add sublimb coverage when missing explicit definition
828  for( armor_portion_data &data : obj.armor->sub_data ) {
829  // if no sub locations are specified assume it covers everything
830  if( data.covers.has_value() && data.sub_coverage.empty() ) {
831  for( const bodypart_str_id &bp : data.covers.value() ) {
832  for( const sub_bodypart_str_id &sbp : bp->sub_parts ) {
833  // only assume to add the non hanging locations
834  if( !sbp->secondary ) {
835  data.sub_coverage.insert( sbp );
836  }
837  }
838  }
839  }
840  }
841 
842  // Include similar sublimbs as well (after populating sub coverage)
843  for( armor_portion_data &data : obj.armor->sub_data ) {
844  std::set<sub_bodypart_str_id> similar_sbp;
845  if( !data.sub_coverage.empty() ) {
846  for( const sub_bodypart_str_id &sbp : data.sub_coverage ) {
847  for( const sub_bodypart_str_id &similar : sbp->similar_bodyparts ) {
848  similar_sbp.emplace( similar );
849  }
850  }
851  }
852  data.sub_coverage.merge( similar_sbp );
853  // We populated substitutes
854  // Handle incomplete matches (ie defined sub coverage without parent coverage)
855  if( !data.sub_coverage.empty() ) {
856  for( const sub_bodypart_str_id &sbp : data.sub_coverage ) {
857  if( !data.covers->test( sbp->parent ) ) {
858  data.covers->set( sbp->parent );
859  }
860  }
861  }
862  }
863 
864 
865  // if this armor doesn't have material info should try to populate it with base item materials
866  for( armor_portion_data &data : obj.armor->sub_data ) {
867  if( data.materials.empty() ) {
868  // if no portion info defined skip scaling for portions
869  bool skip_scale = obj.mat_portion_total == 0;
870  for( const auto &m : obj.materials ) {
871  float factor = skip_scale
872  ? obj.materials.size()
873  : static_cast<float>( m.second ) / static_cast<float>( obj.mat_portion_total );
874  part_material pm( m.first, 100, factor * data.avg_thickness );
875  // need to ignore sheet thickness since inferred thicknesses are not gonna be perfect
876  pm.ignore_sheet_thickness = true;
877  data.materials.push_back( pm );
878  }
879  }
880  }
881 
882  // cache some values and entries before consolidating info per limb
883  for( armor_portion_data &data : obj.armor->sub_data ) {
884  // Setting max_encumber must be in finalize_post because it relies on
885  // stack_size being set for all ammo, which happens in finalize_pre.
886  if( data.max_encumber == -1 ) {
887  units::volume total_nonrigid_volume = 0_ml;
888  for( const pocket_data &pocket : obj.pockets ) {
889  if( !pocket.rigid ) {
890  // include the modifier for each individual pocket
891  total_nonrigid_volume += pocket.max_contains_volume() * pocket.volume_encumber_modifier;
892  }
893  }
894  data.max_encumber = data.encumber + total_nonrigid_volume * data.volume_encumber_modifier /
895  armor_portion_data::volume_per_encumbrance;
896  }
897 
898  // Precalc average thickness per portion
899  int data_count = 0;
900  float thic_acc = 0.0f;
901  for( part_material &m : data.materials ) {
902  thic_acc += m.thickness * m.cover / 100.0f;
903  data_count++;
904  }
905  if( data_count > 0 && thic_acc > std::numeric_limits<float>::epsilon() ) {
906  data.avg_thickness = thic_acc;
907  }
908 
909  // Precalc hardness and comfort for these parts of the armor. uncomfortable material supersedes softness (all rigid materials are assumed to be uncomfy)
910  for( const part_material &m : data.materials ) {
911  if( m.cover > islot_armor::test_threshold ) {
912  if( m.id->soft() ) {
913  data.comfortable = true;
914  } else {
915  data.rigid = true;
916  }
917  if( m.id->uncomfortable() ) {
918  data.comfortable = false;
919  }
920  }
921  }
922  }
923 
924  for( auto itt = obj.armor->sub_data.begin(); itt != obj.armor->sub_data.end(); ++itt ) {
925  // using empty to signify it has already been consolidated
926  if( !itt->sub_coverage.empty() ) {
927  //check if any further entries should be combined with this one
928  for( auto comp_itt = std::next( itt ); comp_itt != obj.armor->sub_data.end(); ++comp_itt ) {
929  if( armor_portion_data::should_consolidate( *itt, *comp_itt ) ) {
930  // they are the same so add the covers and sub covers to the original and then clear them from the other
931  itt->covers->unify_set( comp_itt->covers.value() );
932  itt->sub_coverage.insert( comp_itt->sub_coverage.begin(), comp_itt->sub_coverage.end() );
933  comp_itt->covers->clear();
934  comp_itt->sub_coverage.clear();
935  }
936  }
937  }
938  }
939  //remove any now empty entries
940  auto remove_itt = std::remove_if( obj.armor->sub_data.begin(),
941  obj.armor->sub_data.end(), [&]( const armor_portion_data & data ) {
942  return data.sub_coverage.empty() && data.covers.value().none();
943  } );
944  obj.armor->sub_data.erase( remove_itt, obj.armor->sub_data.end() );
945 
946  // now consolidate all the loaded sub_data to one entry per body part
947  for( const armor_portion_data &sub_armor : obj.armor->sub_data ) {
948  // for each body part this covers we need to add to the overall data for that bp
949  if( sub_armor.covers.has_value() ) {
950  for( const bodypart_str_id &bp : sub_armor.covers.value() ) {
951  bool found = false;
952  // go through and find if the body part already exists
953 
954  for( armor_portion_data &it : obj.armor->data ) {
955  // if it contains the body part update the values with data from this
956  //body_part_set set = it.covers.value();
957  if( it.covers->test( bp ) ) {
958  found = true;
959  // modify the values with additional info
960 
961  it.encumber += sub_armor.encumber;
962  it.max_encumber += sub_armor.max_encumber;
963 
964  for( const encumbrance_modifier &en : sub_armor.encumber_modifiers ) {
965  it.encumber_modifiers.push_back( en );
966  }
967 
968  // get the amount of the limb that is covered with sublocations
969  // for overall coverage we need to scale coverage by that
970  float scale = sub_armor.max_coverage( bp ) / 100.0;
971 
972  float it_scale = it.max_coverage( bp ) / 100.0;
973 
974  it.coverage += sub_armor.coverage * scale;
975  it.cover_melee += sub_armor.cover_melee * scale;
976  it.cover_ranged += sub_armor.cover_ranged * scale;
977  it.cover_vitals += sub_armor.cover_vitals;
978 
979  // these values need to be averaged based on proportion covered
980  it.avg_thickness = ( sub_armor.avg_thickness * scale + it.avg_thickness * it_scale ) /
981  ( scale + it_scale );
982  it.env_resist = ( sub_armor.env_resist * scale + it.env_resist * it_scale ) /
983  ( scale + it_scale );
984  it.env_resist_w_filter = ( sub_armor.env_resist_w_filter * scale + it.env_resist_w_filter *
985  it_scale ) / ( scale + it_scale );
986 
987  // add layers that are covered by sublimbs
988  for( const layer_level &ll : sub_armor.layers ) {
989  it.layers.insert( ll );
990  }
991 
992  // if you are trying to add a new data entry and either the original data
993  // or the new data has an empty sublocations list then say that you are
994  // redefining a limb
995  if( it.sub_coverage.empty() || sub_armor.sub_coverage.empty() ) {
996  debugmsg( "item %s has multiple entries for %s.",
997  obj.id.str(), bp.str() );
998  }
999 
1000  // go through the materials list and update data
1001  for( const part_material &new_mat : sub_armor.materials ) {
1002  bool mat_found = false;
1003  for( part_material &old_mat : it.materials ) {
1004  if( old_mat.id == new_mat.id ) {
1005  mat_found = true;
1006  // values should be averaged
1007  float max_coverage_new = sub_armor.max_coverage( bp );
1008  float max_coverage_mats = it.max_coverage( bp );
1009 
1010  // the percent of the coverable bits that this armor does cover
1011  float coverage_multiplier = sub_armor.coverage * max_coverage_new / 100.0f;
1012 
1013  // portion should be handled as the portion scaled by relative coverage
1014  old_mat.cover = old_mat.cover + static_cast<float>( new_mat.cover ) * coverage_multiplier / 100.0f;
1015 
1016  // with the max values we can get the weight that each should have
1017  old_mat.thickness = ( max_coverage_new * new_mat.thickness + max_coverage_mats *
1018  old_mat.thickness ) / ( max_coverage_mats + max_coverage_new );
1019  }
1020  }
1021  // if we didn't find an entry for this material
1022  // create new entry with a scaled material coverage
1023  if( !mat_found ) {
1024  float max_coverage_new = sub_armor.max_coverage( bp );
1025 
1026  // the percent of the coverable bits that this armor does cover
1027  float coverage_multiplier = sub_armor.coverage * max_coverage_new / 100.0f;
1028 
1029  part_material modified_mat = new_mat;
1030  // if for example your elbow was covered in plastic but none of the rest of the arm
1031  // this should be represented correctly in the UI with the covers for plastic being 5%
1032  // of the arm. Similarily 50% covered in plastic covering only 30% of the arm should lead to
1033  // 15% covered for the arm overall
1034  modified_mat.cover = static_cast<float>( new_mat.cover ) * coverage_multiplier / 100.0f;
1035  it.materials.push_back( modified_mat );
1036  }
1037  }
1038 
1039  // add additional sub coverage locations to the original list
1040  for( const sub_bodypart_str_id &sbp : sub_armor.sub_coverage ) {
1041  it.sub_coverage.insert( sbp );
1042  }
1043  }
1044  }
1045 
1046  // if not found create a new bp entry
1047  if( !found ) {
1048  // copy values to data but only have one limb
1049  armor_portion_data new_limb = sub_armor;
1050  new_limb.covers->clear();
1051  new_limb.covers->set( bp );
1052 
1053  // get the amount of the limb that is covered with sublocations
1054  // for overall coverage we need to scale coverage by that
1055  float scale = new_limb.max_coverage( bp ) / 100.0;
1056 
1057  new_limb.coverage = new_limb.coverage * scale;
1058  new_limb.cover_melee = new_limb.cover_melee * scale;
1059  new_limb.cover_ranged = new_limb.cover_ranged * scale;
1060 
1061  // need to scale each material coverage the same way since they will after this be
1062  // scaled back up at the end of the amalgamation
1063  for( part_material &mat : new_limb.materials ) {
1064  mat.cover = static_cast<float>( mat.cover ) * new_limb.coverage / 100.0f;
1065  }
1066 
1067  obj.armor->data.push_back( new_limb );
1068  }
1069  }
1070  }
1071 
1072  }
1073 
1074  // calculate encumbrance data per limb if done by description
1075  for( armor_portion_data &data : obj.armor->data ) {
1076  if( !data.encumber_modifiers.empty() ) {
1077  // we know that the data entry covers a single bp
1078  data.encumber = data.calc_encumbrance( obj.weight, *data.covers.value().begin() );
1079 
1080  // need to account for varsize stuff here and double encumbrance if so
1081  if( obj.has_flag( flag_VARSIZE ) ) {
1082  data.encumber = std::min( data.encumber * 2, data.encumber + 10 );
1083  }
1084 
1085  // Recalc max encumber as well
1086  units::volume total_nonrigid_volume = 0_ml;
1087  for( const pocket_data &pocket : obj.pockets ) {
1088  if( !pocket.rigid ) {
1089  // include the modifier for each individual pocket
1090  total_nonrigid_volume += pocket.max_contains_volume() * pocket.volume_encumber_modifier;
1091  }
1092  }
1093  data.max_encumber = data.encumber + total_nonrigid_volume * data.volume_encumber_modifier /
1094  armor_portion_data::volume_per_encumbrance;
1095  }
1096  }
1097 
1098  // need to scale amalgamized portion data based on total coverage.
1099  // 3% of 48% needs to be scaled to 6% of 100%
1100  for( armor_portion_data &it : obj.armor->data ) {
1101  for( part_material &mat : it.materials ) {
1102  // scale the value of portion covered based on how much total is covered
1103  // if you proportionally only cover 5% of the arm but overall cover 50%
1104  // you actually proportionally cover 10% of the armor
1105 
1106  // in case of 0 coverage just say the mats cover it all
1107  if( it.coverage == 0 ) {
1108  mat.cover = 100;
1109  } else {
1110  mat.cover = std::round( static_cast<float>( mat.cover ) / ( static_cast<float>
1111  ( it.coverage ) / 100.0f ) );
1112  }
1113  }
1114  }
1115 
1116  // store a shorthand var for if the item has notable sub coverage data
1117  for( const armor_portion_data &armor_data : obj.armor->data ) {
1118  if( obj.armor->has_sub_coverage ) {
1119  // if we already know it has subcoverage break from the loop
1120  break;
1121  }
1122 
1123  // if the item covers everything it doesn't have specific sub coverage
1124  // so don't need to display it in the UI and do tests for it
1125  if( !armor_data.sub_coverage.empty() ) {
1126  // go through and see if we are missing any sublocations
1127  // if we are missing some then the item does cover specific locations
1128  // this flag is mostly used to skip itterating and testing
1129  // if UI should be displayed
1130 
1131  // each armor data entry covers exactly 1 body part
1132  for( const sub_bodypart_str_id &compare_sbp : armor_data.covers->begin()->obj().sub_parts ) {
1133  if( compare_sbp->secondary ) {
1134  // don't care about secondary locations
1135  continue;
1136  }
1137  bool found = false;
1138  for( const sub_bodypart_str_id &sbp : armor_data.sub_coverage ) {
1139  if( compare_sbp == sbp ) {
1140  found = true;
1141  }
1142  }
1143  // if an entry is not found we cover specific parts so this item has sub_coverage
1144  if( !found ) {
1145  obj.armor->has_sub_coverage = true;
1146  }
1147  }
1148  }
1149  }
1150 
1151  // calculate worst case and best case protection %
1152  for( armor_portion_data &armor_data : obj.armor->data ) {
1153  // go through each material and contribute its values
1154  float tempbest = 1.0f;
1155  float tempworst = 1.0f;
1156  for( const part_material &mat : armor_data.materials ) {
1157  // the percent chance the material is not hit
1158  float cover = mat.cover * .01f;
1159  float cover_invert = 1.0f - cover;
1160 
1161  tempbest *= cover;
1162  // just interested in cover values that can fail.
1163  // multiplying by 0 would make this value pointless
1164  if( cover_invert > 0 ) {
1165  tempworst *= cover_invert;
1166  }
1167  }
1168 
1169  // if tempworst is 1 then the item is homogenous so it only has a single option for damage
1170  if( tempworst == 1 ) {
1171  tempworst = 0;
1172  }
1173 
1174  // if not exactly 0 it should display as at least 1
1175  if( tempworst > 0 ) {
1176  armor_data.worst_protection_chance = std::max( 1.0f, tempworst * 100.0f );
1177  } else {
1178  armor_data.worst_protection_chance = 0;
1179  }
1180  if( tempbest > 0 ) {
1181  armor_data.best_protection_chance = std::max( 1.0f, tempbest * 100.0f );
1182  } else {
1183  armor_data.best_protection_chance = 0;
1184  }
1185  }
1186 
1187  // calculate worst case and best case protection %
1188  for( armor_portion_data &armor_data : obj.armor->sub_data ) {
1189  // go through each material and contribute its values
1190  float tempbest = 1.0f;
1191  float tempworst = 1.0f;
1192  for( const part_material &mat : armor_data.materials ) {
1193  // the percent chance the material is not hit
1194  float cover = mat.cover * .01f;
1195  float cover_invert = 1.0f - cover;
1196 
1197  tempbest *= cover;
1198  // just interested in cover values that can fail.
1199  // multiplying by 0 would make this value pointless
1200  if( cover_invert > 0 ) {
1201  tempworst *= cover_invert;
1202  }
1203  }
1204 
1205  // if tempworst is 1 then the item is homogenous so it only has a single option for damage
1206  if( tempworst == 1 ) {
1207  tempworst = 0;
1208  }
1209 
1210  // if not exactly 0 it should display as at least 1
1211  if( tempworst > 0 ) {
1212  armor_data.worst_protection_chance = std::max( 1.0f, tempworst * 100.0f );
1213  } else {
1214  armor_data.worst_protection_chance = 0;
1215  }
1216  if( tempbest > 0 ) {
1217  armor_data.best_protection_chance = std::max( 1.0f, tempbest * 100.0f );
1218  } else {
1219  armor_data.best_protection_chance = 0;
1220  }
1221  }
1222 
1223  // create the vector of all layers
1224  if( obj.has_flag( flag_PERSONAL ) ) {
1225  obj.armor->all_layers.push_back( layer_level::PERSONAL );
1226  }
1227  if( obj.has_flag( flag_SKINTIGHT ) ) {
1228  obj.armor->all_layers.push_back( layer_level::SKINTIGHT );
1229  }
1230  if( obj.has_flag( flag_NORMAL ) ) {
1231  obj.armor->all_layers.push_back( layer_level::NORMAL );
1232  }
1233  if( obj.has_flag( flag_WAIST ) ) {
1234  obj.armor->all_layers.push_back( layer_level::WAIST );
1235  }
1236  if( obj.has_flag( flag_OUTER ) ) {
1237  obj.armor->all_layers.push_back( layer_level::OUTER );
1238  }
1239  if( obj.has_flag( flag_BELTED ) ) {
1240  obj.armor->all_layers.push_back( layer_level::BELTED );
1241  }
1242  if( obj.has_flag( flag_AURA ) ) {
1243  obj.armor->all_layers.push_back( layer_level::AURA );
1244  }
1245  // fallback for old way of doing items
1246  if( obj.armor->all_layers.empty() ) {
1247  obj.armor->all_layers.push_back( layer_level::NORMAL );
1248  }
1249 
1250  // generate the vector of flags that the item will default to if not override
1251  std::vector<layer_level> default_layers = obj.armor->all_layers;
1252 
1253  for( armor_portion_data &armor_data : obj.armor->data ) {
1254  // if an item or location has no layer data then default to the flags for the item
1255  if( armor_data.layers.empty() ) {
1256  for( const layer_level &ll : default_layers ) {
1257  armor_data.layers.insert( ll );
1258  }
1259  } else {
1260  armor_data.has_unique_layering = true;
1261  // add any unique layer entries to the items total layer info
1262  for( const layer_level &ll : armor_data.layers ) {
1263  if( std::count( obj.armor->all_layers.begin(), obj.armor->all_layers.end(), ll ) == 0 ) {
1264  obj.armor->all_layers.push_back( ll );
1265  }
1266  }
1267  }
1268  }
1269  for( armor_portion_data &armor_data : obj.armor->sub_data ) {
1270  // if an item or location has no layer data then default to the flags for the item
1271  if( armor_data.layers.empty() ) {
1272  for( const layer_level &ll : default_layers ) {
1273  armor_data.layers.insert( ll );
1274  }
1275  } else {
1276  armor_data.has_unique_layering = true;
1277  }
1278  }
1279 
1280  // anything on a non traditional clothing layer can't be "rigid" as well since it's storage pouches and stuff
1281  for( armor_portion_data &armor_data : obj.armor->sub_data ) {
1282  auto clothing_layer = std::find_if( armor_data.layers.begin(),
1283  armor_data.layers.end(), []( const layer_level ll ) {
1284  return ll == layer_level::SKINTIGHT || ll == layer_level::NORMAL || ll == layer_level::OUTER;
1285  } );
1286  if( clothing_layer == armor_data.layers.end() ) {
1287  armor_data.rigid = false;
1288  }
1289  }
1290 
1291  bool all_rigid = true;
1292  bool all_comfortable = true;
1293  for( armor_portion_data &data : obj.armor->sub_data ) {
1294  // check if everything on this armor is still rigid / comfortable
1295  all_rigid = all_rigid && data.rigid;
1296  all_comfortable = all_comfortable && data.comfortable;
1297  }
1298  obj.armor->rigid = all_rigid;
1299  obj.armor->comfortable = all_comfortable;
1300 
1301  // go through the pockets and apply some characteristics
1302  for( const pocket_data &pocket : obj.pockets ) {
1303  if( pocket.ablative ) {
1304  obj.armor->ablative = true;
1305  break;
1306  }
1307  if( pocket.extra_encumbrance > 0 ) {
1308  obj.armor->additional_pocket_enc = true;
1309  }
1310  if( pocket.ripoff > 0 ) {
1311  obj.armor->ripoff_chance = true;
1312  }
1313  if( pocket.activity_noise.chance > 0 ) {
1314  obj.armor->noisy = true;
1315  }
1316  }
1317 
1318  // update the items materials based on the materials defined by the armor
1319  // this isn't perfect but neither is the usual definition so this should at
1320  // least give a good ballpark
1321  if( obj.materials.empty() ) {
1322  obj.mat_portion_total = 0;
1323  for( const armor_portion_data &armor_data : obj.armor->data ) {
1324  for( const part_material &mat : armor_data.materials ) {
1325  // if the material isn't in the map yet
1326  if( obj.materials.find( mat.id ) == obj.materials.end() ) {
1327  obj.materials[mat.id] = mat.thickness * 100;
1328  } else {
1329  obj.materials[mat.id] += mat.thickness * 100;
1330  }
1331  obj.mat_portion_total += mat.thickness * 100;
1332  }
1333  }
1334  }
1335 
1336  // calculate each body part breathability of the armor
1337  // breathability is the worst breathability of any material on that portion
1338  for( armor_portion_data &armor_data : obj.armor->data ) {
1339  // only recalculate the breathability when the value is not set in JSON
1340  // or when the value in JSON is invalid
1341  if( armor_data.breathability < 0 ) {
1342 
1343  std::vector<part_material> sorted_mats = armor_data.materials;
1344  std::sort( sorted_mats.begin(), sorted_mats.end(), []( const part_material & lhs,
1345  const part_material & rhs ) {
1346  return lhs.id->breathability() < rhs.id->breathability();
1347  } );
1348 
1349  // now that mats are sorted least breathable to most
1350  int coverage_counted = 0;
1351  int combined_breathability = 0;
1352 
1353  // only calcuate the breathability if the armor has no valid loaded value
1354  for( const part_material &mat : sorted_mats ) {
1355  // this isn't perfect since its impossible to know the positions of each material relatively
1356  // so some guessing is done
1357  // specifically count the worst breathability then then next best with additional coverage
1358  // and repeat until out of matts or fully covering.
1359  combined_breathability += std::max( ( mat.cover - coverage_counted ) * mat.id->breathability(), 0 );
1360  coverage_counted = std::max( mat.cover, coverage_counted );
1361 
1362  // this covers the whole piece of armor so we can stop counting better breathability
1363  if( coverage_counted == 100 ) {
1364  break;
1365  }
1366  }
1367  // whatever isn't covered is as good as skin so 100%
1368  armor_data.breathability = ( combined_breathability / 100 ) + ( 100 - coverage_counted );
1369  }
1370  }
1371 
1372  for( const armor_portion_data &armor_data : obj.armor->data ) {
1373  for( const part_material &mat : armor_data.materials ) {
1374  if( mat.cover > 100 || mat.cover < 0 ) {
1375  debugmsg( "item %s has coverage %d for material %s.",
1376  obj.id.str(), mat.cover, mat.id.str() );
1377  }
1378  }
1379  }
1380 }
1381 
1382 void Item_factory::finalize()
1383 {
1384  DynamicDataLoader::get_instance().load_deferred( deferred );
1385 
1386  finalize_item_blacklist();
1387 
1388  // we can no longer add or adjust static item templates
1389  frozen = true;
1390 
1391  for( auto &e : m_templates ) {
1392  finalize_pre( e.second );
1393  register_cached_uses( e.second );
1394  }
1395 
1396  for( auto &e : m_templates ) {
1397  finalize_post( e.second );
1398  }
1399 
1400  // We may actually have some runtimes here - ones loaded from saved game
1401  // TODO: support for runtimes that repair
1402  for( auto &e : m_runtimes ) {
1403  finalize_pre( *e.second );
1404  finalize_post( *e.second );
1405  }
1406 
1407  // for each item register all (non-obsolete) potential recipes
1408  for( const std::pair<const recipe_id, recipe> &p : recipe_dict ) {
1409  const recipe &rec = p.second;
1410  if( rec.obsolete || rec.will_be_blacklisted() ) {
1411  continue;
1412  }
1413  const itype_id &result = rec.result();
1414  auto it = m_templates.find( result );
1415  if( it != m_templates.end() ) {
1416  it->second.recipes.push_back( p.first );
1417  }
1418  }
1419  for( auto &e : m_template_groups ) {
1420  auto &isd = e.second;
1421  isd->finalize( itype_id::NULL_ID() );
1422  }
1423 }
1424 void item_blacklist_t::clear()
1425 {
1426  blacklist.clear();
1427  sub_blacklist.clear();
1428 }
1429 
1430 void Item_factory::finalize_item_blacklist()
1431 {
1432  // Populate a whitelist, and a blacklist with items on whitelists and items on blacklists
1433  std::set<itype_id> whitelist;
1434  for( const std::pair<bool, std::set<itype_id>> &blacklist : item_blacklist.sub_blacklist ) {
1435  // True == whitelist, false == blacklist
1436  if( blacklist.first ) {
1437  whitelist.insert( blacklist.second.begin(), blacklist.second.end() );
1438  } else {
1439  item_blacklist.blacklist.insert( blacklist.second.begin(), blacklist.second.end() );
1440  }
1441  }
1442 
1443  bool whitelist_exists = !whitelist.empty();
1444  // Remove all blacklisted items on the whitelist
1445  std::set<itype_id> &blacklist = item_blacklist.blacklist;
1446  for( const itype_id &it : whitelist ) {
1447  if( blacklist.count( it ) ) {
1448  whitelist.erase( it );
1449  }
1450  }
1451 
1452  // Now, populate the blacklist with all the items that aren't whitelists, but only if a whitelist exists.
1453  if( whitelist_exists ) {
1454  blacklist.clear();
1455  for( const std::pair<const itype_id, itype> &item : m_templates ) {
1456  if( !whitelist.count( item.first ) ) {
1457  blacklist.insert( item.first );
1458  }
1459  }
1460  }
1461 
1462  // And clear the blacklists we made in-between
1463  item_blacklist.sub_blacklist.clear();
1464 
1465  for( const itype_id &blackout : item_blacklist.blacklist ) {
1466  std::unordered_map<itype_id, itype>::iterator candidate = m_templates.find( blackout );
1467  if( candidate == m_templates.end() ) {
1468  debugmsg( "item on blacklist %s does not exist", blackout.c_str() );
1469  continue;
1470  }
1471 
1472  for( std::pair<const item_group_id, std::unique_ptr<Item_spawn_data>> &g : m_template_groups ) {
1473  g.second->remove_item( candidate->first );
1474  }
1475 
1476  // remove any blacklisted items from requirements
1477  for( const std::pair<const requirement_id, requirement_data> &r : requirement_data::all() ) {
1478  const_cast<requirement_data &>( r.second ).blacklist_item( candidate->first );
1479  }
1480 
1481  // remove any recipes used to craft the blacklisted item
1482  recipe_dictionary::delete_if( [&candidate]( const recipe & r ) {
1483  return r.result() == candidate->first;
1484  } );
1485  }
1486  for( const vehicle_prototype &const_prototype : vehicles::get_all_prototypes() ) {
1487  vehicle_prototype &prototype = const_cast<vehicle_prototype &>( const_prototype );
1488  for( vehicle_item_spawn &vis : prototype.item_spawns ) {
1489  auto &vec = vis.item_ids;
1490  const auto iter = std::remove_if( vec.begin(), vec.end(), item_is_blacklisted );
1491  vec.erase( iter, vec.end() );
1492  }
1493  }
1494 
1495  // Construct a map for batch item replace
1496  std::unordered_map<itype_id, itype_id> replacements;
1497  for( const std::pair<const itype_id, std::vector<migration>> &migrate : migrations ) {
1498  // The valid migration entry
1499  const migration *valid = nullptr;
1500  for( const migration &cand : migrate.second ) {
1501  // This can only be applied to items, not itypes
1502  if( cand.from_variant ) {
1503  continue;
1504  }
1505  // There can only be one migration entry
1506  if( valid == nullptr ) {
1507  valid = &cand;
1508  } else {
1509  valid = nullptr;
1510  break;
1511  }
1512  }
1513  // Either there are no migrations, or too many migrations
1514  // Errors are reported below
1515  if( valid == nullptr ) {
1516  continue;
1517  }
1518  if( m_templates.count( valid->replace ) == 0 ) {
1519  // Errors for missing item templates will be reported below
1520  continue;
1521  }
1522  replacements[migrate.first] = valid->replace;
1523  }
1524  // Replace items in item template groups
1525  for( std::pair<const item_group_id, std::unique_ptr<Item_spawn_data>> &g : m_template_groups ) {
1526  g.second->replace_items( replacements );
1527  }
1528  // Replace templates in recipe/part/etc. requirements
1529  for( const std::pair<const requirement_id, requirement_data> &r : requirement_data::all() ) {
1530  const_cast<requirement_data &>( r.second ).replace_items( replacements );
1531  }
1532 
1533  for( const std::pair<const itype_id, std::vector<migration>> &migrate : migrations ) {
1534  const migration *parent = nullptr;
1535  for( const migration &migrant : migrate.second ) {
1536  if( m_templates.count( migrant.replace ) == 0 ) {
1537  debugmsg( "Replacement item (%s) for migration %s does not exist", migrant.replace.str(),
1538  migrate.first.c_str() );
1539  continue;
1540  }
1541  // The rest of this only applies to blanket migrations
1542  // Not migrations looking for a particular variant
1543  if( migrant.from_variant ) {
1544  continue;
1545  }
1546  if( parent != nullptr ) {
1547  debugmsg( "Multiple non-variant migrations specified for %s", migrate.first.str() );
1548  }
1549  parent = &migrant;
1550  }
1551  // Only variant migrations exist, abort
1552  if( parent == nullptr ) {
1553  continue;
1554  }
1555 
1556  // remove any recipes used to craft the migrated item
1557  // if there's a valid recipe, it will be for the replacement
1558  recipe_dictionary::delete_if( [&migrate]( const recipe & r ) {
1559  return !r.obsolete && r.result() == migrate.first;
1560  } );
1561 
1562  // If the default ammo of an ammo_type gets migrated, we migrate all guns using that ammo
1563  // type to the ammo type of whatever that default ammo was migrated to.
1564  // To do that we need to store a map of ammo to the migration replacement thereof.
1565  auto maybe_ammo = m_templates.find( migrate.first );
1566  // If the itype_id is valid and the itype has ammo data
1567  if( maybe_ammo != m_templates.end() && maybe_ammo->second.ammo ) {
1568  auto replacement = m_templates.find( parent->replace );
1569  if( replacement->second.ammo ) {
1570  migrated_ammo.emplace( migrate.first, replacement->second.ammo->type );
1571  } else {
1572  debugmsg( "Replacement item %s for migrated ammo %s is not ammo.",
1573  parent->replace.str(), migrate.first.str() );
1574  }
1575  }
1576 
1577  // migrate magazines as well
1578  auto maybe_mag = m_templates.find( migrate.first );
1579  if( maybe_mag != m_templates.end() && maybe_mag->second.magazine ) {
1580  auto replacement = m_templates.find( parent->replace );
1581  if( replacement->second.magazine ) {
1582  migrated_magazines.emplace( migrate.first, parent->replace );
1583  } else {
1584  debugmsg( "Replacement item %s for migrated magazine %s is not a magazine.",
1585  parent->replace.str(), migrate.first.str() );
1586  }
1587  }
1588  }
1589  for( const vehicle_prototype &const_prototype : vehicles::get_all_prototypes() ) {
1590  vehicle_prototype &prototype = const_cast<vehicle_prototype &>( const_prototype );
1591  for( vehicle_item_spawn &vis : prototype.item_spawns ) {
1592  for( itype_id &type_to_spawn : vis.item_ids ) {
1593  std::map<itype_id, std::vector<migration>>::iterator replacement =
1594  migrations.find( type_to_spawn );
1595  if( replacement == migrations.end() ) {
1596  continue;
1597  }
1598  const migration *parent = nullptr;
1599  for( const migration &migrant : replacement->second ) {
1600  if( m_templates.count( migrant.replace ) == 0 ) {
1601  // Error reported above
1602  continue;
1603  }
1604  // The rest of this only applies to blanket migrations
1605  // Not migrations looking for a particular variant
1606  if( migrant.from_variant ) {
1607  continue;
1608  }
1609  if( parent != nullptr ) {
1610  // Error reported above
1611  parent = nullptr;
1612  break;
1613  }
1614  parent = &migrant;
1615  }
1616  if( parent == nullptr ) {
1617  continue;
1618  }
1619  type_to_spawn = parent->replace;
1620  }
1621  }
1622  }
1623 }
1624 
1625 void Item_factory::load_item_blacklist( const JsonObject &json )
1626 {
1627  bool whitelist = json.get_bool( "whitelist" );
1628  std::set<itype_id> tmp_blacklist;
1629  json.read( "items", tmp_blacklist, true );
1630  item_blacklist.sub_blacklist.emplace_back( whitelist, tmp_blacklist );
1631 }

1640 class iuse_function_wrapper : public iuse_actor
1641 {
1642  private:
1643  use_function_pointer cpp_function;
1644  public:
1645  iuse_function_wrapper( const std::string &type, const use_function_pointer f )
1646  : iuse_actor( type ), cpp_function( f ) { }
1647 
1648  ~iuse_function_wrapper() override = default;
1649  std::optional<int> use( Character *p, item &it, const tripoint &pos ) const override {
1650  return cpp_function( p, &it, pos );
1651  }
1652  std::unique_ptr<iuse_actor> clone() const override {
1653  return std::make_unique<iuse_function_wrapper>( *this );
1654  }
1655 
1656  void load( const JsonObject & ) override {}
1657 };
1658 
1659 class iuse_function_wrapper_with_info : public iuse_function_wrapper
1660 {
1661  private:
1662  translation info_string;
1663  public:
1664  iuse_function_wrapper_with_info(
1665  const std::string &type, const use_function_pointer f, const translation &info )
1666  : iuse_function_wrapper( type, f ), info_string( info ) { }
1667 
1668  void info( const item &, std::vector<iteminfo> &info ) const override {
1669  info.emplace_back( "DESCRIPTION", info_string.translated() );
1670  }
1671  std::unique_ptr<iuse_actor> clone() const override {
1672  return std::make_unique<iuse_function_wrapper_with_info>( *this );
1673  }
1674 };

1696 
1697 void Item_factory::add_item_type( const itype &def )
1698 {
1699  if( m_runtimes.count( def.id ) > 0 ) {
1700  // Do NOT allow overwriting it, it's undefined behavior
1701  debugmsg( "Tried to add runtime type %s, but it exists already", def.id.c_str() );
1702  return;
1703  }
1704 
1705  auto &new_item_ptr = m_runtimes[ def.id ];
1706  new_item_ptr = std::make_unique<itype>( def );
1707  if( frozen ) {
1708  finalize_pre( *new_item_ptr );
1709  finalize_post( *new_item_ptr );
1710  }
1711 }
