1939 
1940 bool Item_factory::check_ammo_type( std::string &msg, const ammotype &ammo ) const
1941 {
1942  if( ammo.is_null() ) {
1943  return false;
1944  }
1945 
1946  if( !ammo.is_valid() ) {
1947  msg += string_format( "ammo type %s is not known\n", ammo.c_str() );
1948  return false;
1949  }
1950 
1951  if( std::none_of( m_templates.begin(),
1952  m_templates.end(), [&ammo]( const decltype( m_templates )::value_type & e ) {
1953  return e.second.ammo && e.second.ammo->type == ammo;
1954 } ) ) {
1955  msg += string_format( "there is no actual ammo of type %s defined\n", ammo.c_str() );
1956  return false;
1957  }
1958  return true;
1959 }
1960 
1961 void Item_factory::check_definitions() const
1962 {
1963  auto is_container = []( const itype * t ) {
1964  bool am_container = false;
1965  for( const pocket_data &pocket : t->pockets ) {
1966  if( pocket.type == pocket_type::CONTAINER ) {
1967  am_container = true;
1968  // no need to look further
1969  break;
1970  }
1971  }
1972  return am_container;
1973  };
1974 
1975  for( const auto &elem : m_templates ) {
1976  std::string msg;
1977  const itype *type = &elem.second;
1978 
1979  if( !type->has_flag( flag_TARDIS ) ) {
1980  if( is_container( type ) ) {
1981  units::volume volume = type->volume;
1982  if( type->count_by_charges() ) {
1983  volume /= type->charges_default();
1984  }
1985  if( item_contents( type->pockets ).bigger_on_the_inside( volume ) ) {
1986  msg += "is bigger on the inside. consider using TARDIS flag.\n";
1987  }
1988  }
1989  }
1990 
1991  if( !type->picture_id.is_empty() && !type->picture_id.is_valid() ) {
1992  msg += "item has unknown ascii_picture.";
1993  }
1994 
1995  int mag_pocket_number = 0;
1996  for( const pocket_data &data : type->pockets ) {
1997  if( data.type == pocket_type::MAGAZINE ||
1998  data.type == pocket_type::MAGAZINE_WELL ) {
1999  mag_pocket_number++;
2000  }
2001  std::string pocket_error = data.check_definition();
2002  if( !pocket_error.empty() ) {
2003  msg += "problem with pocket: " + pocket_error;
2004  }
2005  }
2006  if( mag_pocket_number > 1 ) {
2007  msg += "cannot have more than one pocket that handles ammo (MAGAZINE or MAGAZINE_WELL)\n";
2008  }
2009 
2010  if( !type->category_force.is_valid() ) {
2011  msg += "undefined category " + type->category_force.str() + "\n";
2012  }
2013 
2014  if( type->armor ) {
2015  cata::flat_set<bodypart_str_id> observed_bps;
2016  for( const armor_portion_data &portion : type->armor->data ) {
2017  if( portion.covers.has_value() ) {
2018  for( const bodypart_str_id &bp : *portion.covers ) {
2019  if( portion.covers->test( bp ) ) {
2020  if( observed_bps.count( bp ) ) {
2021  msg += string_format(
2022  "multiple portions with same body_part %s defined\n",
2023  bp.str() );
2024  }
2025  observed_bps.insert( bp );
2026  }
2027  }
2028  }
2029  if( portion.coverage == 0 && ( portion.cover_melee > 0 || portion.cover_ranged > 0 ) ) {
2030  msg += "base \"coverage\" value not specified in armor portion despite using \"cover_melee\"/\"cover_ranged\"\n";
2031  }
2032  }
2033 
2034  // do tests for the sub bp armor data arrays
2035  std::vector<sub_bodypart_str_id> observed_sub_bps;
2036  for( const armor_portion_data &portion : type->armor->sub_data ) {
2037  for( const sub_bodypart_str_id &bp : portion.sub_coverage ) {
2038  if( std::find( observed_sub_bps.begin(), observed_sub_bps.end(), bp ) != observed_sub_bps.end() ) {
2039  msg += string_format(
2040  "multiple portions with same sub_body_part %s defined\n",
2041  bp.str() );
2042  }
2043  observed_sub_bps.push_back( bp );
2044  }
2045  if( portion.coverage == 0 && ( portion.cover_melee > 0 || portion.cover_ranged > 0 ) ) {
2046  msg += "base \"coverage\" value not specified in armor portion despite using \"cover_melee\"/\"cover_ranged\"\n";
2047  }
2048  }
2049 
2050  // check the hanging location aren't being used on the non strapped layer
2051  if( std::find( type->armor->all_layers.begin(), type->armor->all_layers.end(),
2052  layer_level::BELTED ) == type->armor->all_layers.end() ) {
2053  for( const armor_portion_data &portion : type->armor->sub_data ) {
2054  for( const sub_bodypart_str_id &sbp : portion.sub_coverage ) {
2055  if( sbp->secondary ) {
2056  msg += string_format( "Secondary hanging locations should only be used on the BELTED layer: %s\n",
2057  sbp.str() );
2058  }
2059  }
2060  }
2061  }
2062 
2063  // waist is deprecated
2064  if( type->has_flag( flag_WAIST ) ) {
2065  msg += string_format( "Waist has been deprecated as an armor layer and is now a sublocation of the torso on the BELTED layer. If you are making new content make it BELTED specifically covering the torso_waist. If you are loading an old mod you are probably safe to ignore this.\n" );
2066  }
2067 
2068  // check that no item has more coverage on any location than the max coverage (100)
2069  for( const armor_portion_data &portion : type->armor->sub_data ) {
2070  if( 100 < portion.coverage || 100 < portion.cover_melee ||
2071  100 < portion.cover_ranged ) {
2072  msg += string_format( "coverage exceeds the maximum amount for the sub locations coverage can't exceed 100, item coverage: %d\n",
2073  portion.coverage );
2074  }
2075  }
2076  // check that no item has more coverage on any location than the max coverage (100)
2077  for( const armor_portion_data &portion : type->armor->data ) {
2078  if( 100 < portion.coverage || 100 < portion.cover_melee ||
2079  100 < portion.cover_ranged ) {
2080  msg += string_format( "coverage exceeds the maximum amount for the locations coverage can't exceed 100, item coverage: %d\n",
2081  portion.coverage );
2082  }
2083  }
2084  // check that all materials are between 0-100 proportional coverage
2085  for( const armor_portion_data &portion : type->armor->sub_data ) {
2086  for( const part_material &mat : portion.materials ) {
2087  if( mat.cover < 0 || mat.cover > 100 ) {
2088  msg += string_format( "material %s has proportional coverage %d. proportional coverage is a value between 0-100.",
2089  mat.id.str(), mat.cover );
2090  }
2091  }
2092  }
2093 
2094  // check that at least 1 material has 100% coverage on each item
2095  for( const armor_portion_data &portion : type->armor->sub_data ) {
2096  // if the advanced materials entry is empty skip this stuff
2097  if( !portion.materials.empty() ) {
2098  bool found = false;
2099  for( const part_material &mat : portion.materials ) {
2100  if( mat.cover == 100 ) {
2101  found = true;
2102  }
2103  }
2104 
2105  if( !found ) {
2106  msg += string_format( "at least 1 material for any armor entry should have proportional coverage 100. Consider dropping overall coverage to compensate." );
2107  }
2108  }
2109  }
2110  // check each original definition had a valid material thickness
2111  // valid thickness is a multiple of sheet thickness
2112  for( const armor_portion_data &portion : type->armor->sub_data ) {
2113  for( const part_material &mat : portion.materials ) {
2114  if( !mat.ignore_sheet_thickness && !mat.id->is_valid_thickness( mat.thickness ) ) {
2115  msg += string_format( "for material %s, %f isn't a valid multiple of the thickness the underlying material comes in: %f.\n",
2116  mat.id.str(), mat.thickness, mat.id->thickness_multiple() );
2117  }
2118  }
2119  }
2120  }
2121 
2122  for( const std::pair<const damage_type_id, float> &dt : type->melee ) {
2123  if( !dt.first.is_valid() ) {
2124  msg += string_format( "Invalid melee damage type \"%s\".\n", dt.first.c_str() );
2125  }
2126  }
2127 
2128  if( !type->can_have_charges() && type->charges_default() > 0 ) {
2129  msg += "charges defined but can not have any\n";
2130  } else if( type->comestible && type->can_have_charges() && type->charges_default() <= 0 ) {
2131  msg += "charges expected but not defined or <= 0\n";
2132  }
2133 
2134  if( type->weight < 0_gram ) {
2135  msg += "negative weight\n";
2136  }
2137  if( type->weight == 0_gram && is_physical( *type ) ) {
2138  msg += "zero weight (if zero weight is intentional you can "
2139  "suppress this error with the ZERO_WEIGHT flag)\n";
2140  }
2141  if( type->volume < 0_ml ) {
2142  msg += "negative volume\n";
2143  }
2144  if( type->volume > MAX_ITEM_VOLUME ) {
2145  msg += string_format( "exceeds max volume(%s L)\n", units::to_liter( MAX_ITEM_VOLUME ) );
2146  }
2147  if( type->stack_size <= 0 ) {
2148  if( type->count_by_charges() ) {
2149  msg += string_format( "invalid stack_size %d on type using charges\n", type->stack_size );
2150  } else if( type->phase == phase_id::LIQUID ) {
2151  msg += string_format( "invalid stack_size %d on liquid type\n", type->stack_size );
2152  }
2153  }
2154  if( type->price < 0_cent ) {
2155  msg += "negative price\n";
2156  }
2157  if( type->description.empty() ) {
2158  msg += "empty description\n";
2159  }
2160 
2161  for( const std::pair<const material_id, int> &mat_id : type->materials ) {
2162  if( mat_id.first.str() == "null" || !mat_id.first.is_valid() ) {
2163  msg += string_format( "invalid material %s\n", mat_id.first.c_str() );
2164  }
2165  }
2166 
2167  if( type->sym.empty() ) {
2168  msg += "symbol not defined\n";
2169  } else if( utf8_width( type->sym ) != 1 ) {
2170  msg += "symbol must be exactly one console cell width\n";
2171  }
2172 
2173  for( const auto &_a : type->techniques ) {
2174  if( !_a.is_valid() ) {
2175  msg += string_format( "unknown technique %s\n", _a.c_str() );
2176  }
2177  }
2178  if( !type->snippet_category.empty() ) {
2179  if( !SNIPPET.has_category( type->snippet_category ) ) {
2180  msg += string_format( "item %s: snippet category %s without any snippets\n", type->id.c_str(),
2181  type->snippet_category.c_str() );
2182  }
2183  }
2184  for( const auto &q : type->qualities ) {
2185  if( !q.first.is_valid() ) {
2186  msg += string_format( "item %s has unknown quality %s\n", type->id.c_str(),
2187  q.first.c_str() );
2188  }
2189  }
2190  if( type->default_container && !type->default_container->is_null() ) {
2191  if( has_template( *type->default_container ) ) {
2192  // Spawn the item in its default container to generate an error
2193  // if it doesn't fit.
2194  item( type ).in_its_container();
2195  } else {
2196  msg += string_format( "invalid container property %s\n",
2197  type->default_container->c_str() );
2198  }
2199  }
2200 
2201  for( const auto &e : type->emits ) {
2202  if( !e.is_valid() ) {
2203  msg += string_format( "item %s has unknown emit source %s\n", type->id.c_str(), e.c_str() );
2204  }
2205  }
2206 
2207  for( const auto &f : type->faults ) {
2208  if( !f.is_valid() ) {
2209  msg += string_format( "invalid item fault %s\n", f.c_str() );
2210  }
2211  }
2212 
2213  if( type->comestible ) {
2214  if( !type->comestible->tool.is_null() ) {
2215  const itype *req_tool = find_template( type->comestible->tool );
2216  if( !req_tool->tool ) {
2217  msg += string_format( "invalid tool property %s\n", type->comestible->tool.c_str() );
2218  }
2219  }
2220 
2221  // TODO: Remove invalid, just make those items not comestibles
2222  static const std::set<std::string> allowed_ctypes = { "FOOD", "DRINK", "MED", "INVALID" };
2223  if( allowed_ctypes.count( type->comestible->comesttype ) == 0 ) {
2224  msg += string_format( "Invalid comestible type %s\n", type->comestible->comesttype );
2225  }
2226  }
2227  if( type->brewable ) {
2228  if( type->brewable->time < 1_turns ) {
2229  msg += "brewable time is less than 1 turn\n";
2230  }
2231 
2232  if( type->brewable->results.empty() ) {
2233  msg += "empty product list\n";
2234  }
2235 
2236  for( const std::pair<const itype_id, int> &b : type->brewable->results ) {
2237  if( !has_template( b.first ) ) {
2238  msg += string_format( "invalid result id %s\n", b.first.c_str() );
2239  }
2240  }
2241  }
2242  if( type->compostable ) {
2243  if( type->compostable->time < 1_turns ) {
2244  msg += "fermenting time is less than 1 turn\n";
2245  }
2246 
2247  if( type->compostable->results.empty() ) {
2248  msg += "empty product list\n";
2249  }
2250 
2251  for( const std::pair<const itype_id, int> &b : type->compostable->results ) {
2252  if( !has_template( b.first ) ) {
2253  msg += string_format( "invalid result id %s\n", b.first.c_str() );
2254  }
2255  }
2256  }
2257  if( type->seed ) {
2258  if( type->seed->grow < 1_turns ) {
2259  msg += "seed growing time is less than 1 turn\n";
2260  }
2261  if( !has_template( type->seed->fruit_id ) ) {
2262  msg += string_format( "invalid fruit id %s\n", type->seed->fruit_id.c_str() );
2263  }
2264  for( auto &b : type->seed->byproducts ) {
2265  if( !has_template( b ) ) {
2266  msg += string_format( "invalid byproduct id %s\n", b.c_str() );
2267  }
2268  }
2269  }
2270  if( type->book ) {
2271  if( type->book->skill && !type->book->skill.is_valid() ) {
2272  msg += "uses invalid book skill.\n";
2273  }
2274  if( type->book->martial_art && !type->book->martial_art.is_valid() ) {
2275  msg += string_format( "trains invalid martial art '%s'.\n", type->book->martial_art.str() );
2276  }
2277  if( type->can_use( "MA_MANUAL" ) && !type->book->martial_art ) {
2278  msg += "has use_action MA_MANUAL but does not specify a martial art\n";
2279  }
2280  }
2281  if( type->can_use( "MA_MANUAL" ) && !type->book ) {
2282  msg += "has use_action MA_MANUAL but is not a book\n";
2283  }
2284  if( type->milling_data && !type->milling_data->into_.is_null() ) {
2285  if( !has_template( type->milling_data->into_ ) ) {
2286  msg += "type to mill into is invalid: " + type->milling_data->into_.str() + "\n";
2287  }
2288  }
2289  if( type->ammo ) {
2290  if( !type->ammo->type && type->ammo->type != ammo_NULL ) {
2291  msg += "must define at least one ammo type\n";
2292  }
2293  check_ammo_type( msg, type->ammo->type );
2294  if( type->ammo->casing && ( !has_template( *type->ammo->casing ) ||
2295  type->ammo->casing->is_null() ) ) {
2296  msg += string_format( "invalid casing property %s\n", type->ammo->casing->c_str() );
2297  }
2298  if( !type->ammo->drop.is_null() && !has_template( type->ammo->drop ) ) {
2299  msg += string_format( "invalid drop item %s\n", type->ammo->drop.c_str() );
2300  }
2301  if( type->ammo->shot_damage.empty() && type->ammo->count != 1 ) {
2302  msg += string_format( "invalid shot definition, shot count with no shot damage." );
2303  }
2304  if( !type->ammo->shot_damage.empty() && type->ammo->count == 1 ) {
2305  msg += string_format( "invalid shot definition, shot damage with no shot count." );
2306  }
2307  }
2308  if( type->battery ) {
2309  if( type->battery->max_capacity < 0_mJ ) {
2310  msg += "battery cannot have negative maximum charge\n";
2311  }
2312  }
2313  if( type->gun ) {
2314  for( const ammotype &at : type->gun->ammo ) {
2315  check_ammo_type( msg, at );
2316  }
2317  if( type->gun->ammo.empty() ) {
2318  // if gun doesn't use ammo forbid both integral or detachable magazines
2319  if( static_cast<bool>( type->gun->clip ) || !type->magazines.empty() ) {
2320  msg += "cannot specify clip_size or magazine without ammo type\n";
2321  }
2322 
2323  if( type->has_flag( flag_RELOAD_AND_SHOOT ) ) {
2324  msg += "RELOAD_AND_SHOOT requires an ammo type to be specified\n";
2325  }
2326 
2327  } else {
2328  if( type->has_flag( flag_RELOAD_AND_SHOOT ) && !type->magazines.empty() ) {
2329  msg += "RELOAD_AND_SHOOT cannot be used with magazines\n";
2330  }
2331  for( const ammotype &at : type->gun->ammo ) {
2332  if( !type->gun->clip && !type->magazines.empty() && !type->magazine_default.count( at ) ) {
2333  msg += string_format( "specified magazine but none provided for ammo type %s\n", at.str() );
2334  }
2335  }
2336  }
2337  if( type->gun->barrel_volume < 0_ml ) {
2338  msg += "gun barrel volume cannot be negative\n";
2339  }
2340 
2341  if( !type->gun->skill_used ) {
2342  msg += "uses no skill\n";
2343  } else if( !type->gun->skill_used.is_valid() ) {
2344  msg += string_format( "uses an invalid skill %s\n", type->gun->skill_used.str() );
2345  }
2346  for( const itype_id &gm : type->gun->default_mods ) {
2347  if( !has_template( gm ) ) {
2348  msg += "invalid default mod.\n";
2349  }
2350  }
2351  for( const itype_id &gm : type->gun->built_in_mods ) {
2352  if( !has_template( gm ) ) {
2353  msg += "invalid built-in mod.\n";
2354  }
2355  }
2356  }
2357  if( type->gunmod ) {
2358  if( type->gunmod->location.str().empty() ) {
2359  msg += "gunmod does not specify location\n";
2360  }
2361  if( type->gunmod->sight_dispersion >= 0 ) {
2362  if( type->gunmod->field_of_view <= 0 && type->gunmod->aim_speed < 0 ) {
2363  msg += "gunmod must have both sight_dispersion and field_of_view set or neither of them set\n";
2364  } else if( type->gunmod->aim_speed > 0 ) {
2365  msg += "Aim speed will be converted to FoV and aim_speed_modifier automatically, if FoV is not set.\n";
2366  }
2367  } else if( type->gunmod->sight_dispersion < 0 && type->gunmod->field_of_view > 0 ) {
2368  msg += "gunmod must have both sight_dispersion and field_of_view set or neither of them set\n";
2369  }
2370  if( type->gunmod->usable.empty() ) {
2371  msg += "gunmod does not specify mod targets\n";
2372  }
2373  if( type->gunmod->install_time < 0 ) {
2374  msg += "gunmod does not specify install time\n";
2375  }
2376  }
2377  if( type->mod ) {
2378  for( const ammotype &at : type->mod->ammo_modifier ) {
2379  check_ammo_type( msg, at );
2380  }
2381 
2382  for( const auto &e : type->mod->acceptable_ammo ) {
2383  check_ammo_type( msg, e );
2384  }
2385 
2386  for( const auto &e : type->mod->magazine_adaptor ) {
2387  check_ammo_type( msg, e.first );
2388  if( e.second.empty() ) {
2389  msg += string_format( "no magazines specified for ammo type %s\n", e.first.str() );
2390  }
2391  for( const itype_id &opt : e.second ) {
2392  const itype *mag = find_template( opt );
2393  if( !mag->magazine || !mag->magazine->type.count( e.first ) ) {
2394  msg += string_format( "invalid magazine %s in magazine adapter\n", opt.str() );
2395  }
2396  }
2397  }
2398  }
2399  if( type->magazine ) {
2400  for( const ammotype &at : type->magazine->type ) {
2401  check_ammo_type( msg, at );
2402  }
2403  if( type->magazine->type.empty() ) {
2404  msg += "magazine did not specify ammo type\n";
2405  }
2406  if( type->magazine->capacity < 0 ) {
2407  msg += string_format( "invalid capacity %i\n", type->magazine->capacity );
2408  }
2409  if( type->magazine->count < 0 || type->magazine->count > type->magazine->capacity ) {
2410  msg += string_format( "invalid count %i\n", type->magazine->count );
2411  }
2412  const itype_id &default_ammo = type->magazine->default_ammo;
2413  const itype *da = find_template( default_ammo );
2414  if( da->ammo && type->magazine->type.count( da->ammo->type ) ) {
2415  if( !migrations.count( type->id ) && !item_is_blacklisted( type->id ) ) {
2416  // Verify that the default amnmo can actually be put in this
2417  // item
2418  item( type ).ammo_set( default_ammo, 1 );
2419  }
2420  } else {
2421  msg += string_format( "invalid default_ammo %s\n", type->magazine->default_ammo.str() );
2422  }
2423  if( type->magazine->reload_time < 0 ) {
2424  msg += string_format( "invalid reload_time %i\n", type->magazine->reload_time );
2425  }
2426  if( type->magazine->linkage && ( !has_template( *type->magazine->linkage ) ||
2427  type->magazine->linkage->is_null() ) ) {
2428  msg += string_format( "invalid linkage property %s\n", type->magazine->linkage->c_str() );
2429  }
2430  }
2431 
2432  for( const std::pair<const string_id<ammunition_type>, std::set<itype_id>> &ammo_variety :
2433  type->magazines ) {
2434  if( ammo_variety.second.empty() ) {
2435  msg += string_format( "no magazine specified for %s\n", ammo_variety.first.str() );
2436  }
2437  for( const itype_id &magazine : ammo_variety.second ) {
2438  const itype *mag_ptr = find_template( magazine );
2439  if( mag_ptr == nullptr ) {
2440  msg += string_format( "magazine \"%s\" specified for \"%s\" does not exist\n",
2441  magazine.str(), ammo_variety.first.str() );
2442  } else if( !mag_ptr->magazine ) {
2443  msg += string_format(
2444  "magazine \"%s\" specified for \"%s\" is not a magazine\n", magazine.str(),
2445  ammo_variety.first.str() );
2446  } else if( !mag_ptr->magazine->type.count( ammo_variety.first ) ) {
2447  msg += string_format( "magazine \"%s\" does not take compatible ammo\n",
2448  magazine.str() );
2449  } else if( mag_ptr->has_flag( flag_SPEEDLOADER ) &&
2450  mag_ptr->magazine->capacity != type->gun->clip ) {
2451  msg += string_format(
2452  "speedloader %s capacity (%d) does not match gun capacity (%d).\n",
2453  magazine.str(), mag_ptr->magazine->capacity, type->gun->clip );
2454  } else {
2455  // Verify that every magazine type can actually be put in
2456  // this item
2457  item( type ).put_in( item( magazine ), pocket_type::MAGAZINE_WELL );
2458  }
2459  }
2460  }
2461 
2462  if( type->tool ) {
2463  for( const ammotype &at : type->tool->ammo_id ) {
2464  check_ammo_type( msg, at );
2465  }
2466  if( !type->tool->revert_msg.empty() && !type->revert_to ) {
2467  msg += "cannot specify revert_msg without revert_to\n";
2468  }
2469  if( !type->tool->subtype.is_empty() && !has_template( type->tool->subtype ) ) {
2470  msg += string_format( "invalid tool subtype %s\n", type->tool->subtype.str() );
2471  }
2472  }
2473  if( type->bionic ) {
2474  if( !type->bionic->id.is_valid() ) {
2475  msg += string_format( "there is no bionic with id %s\n", type->bionic->id.c_str() );
2476  }
2477  }
2478 
2479  for( const auto &elem : type->use_methods ) {
2480  const iuse_actor *actor = elem.second.get_actor_ptr();
2481 
2482  cata_assert( actor );
2483  if( !actor->is_valid() ) {
2484  msg += string_format( "item action \"%s\" was not described.\n", actor->type.c_str() );
2485  }
2486  }
2487 
2488  if( !migrations.count( type->id ) && !item_is_blacklisted( type->id ) ) {
2489  // If type has a default ammo then check it can fit within
2490  item tmp_item( type );
2491  if( tmp_item.is_gun() || tmp_item.is_magazine() ) {
2492  if( itype_id ammo_id = tmp_item.ammo_default() ) {
2493  tmp_item.ammo_set( ammo_id, 1 );
2494  }
2495  }
2496  }
2497 
2498  if( type->revert_to && ( !has_template( *type->revert_to ) ||
2499  type->revert_to->is_null() ) ) {
2500  msg += string_format( "invalid revert_to property %s\n does not exist", type->revert_to->c_str() );
2501  }
2502 
2503  if( msg.empty() ) {
2504  continue;
2505  }
2506  debugmsg( "warnings for type %s:\n%s", type->id.c_str(), msg );
2507  }
2508  for( const auto &e : migrations ) {
2509  for( const migration &m : e.second ) {
2510  if( !m_templates.count( m.replace ) ) {
2511  debugmsg( "Invalid migration target: %s", m.replace.c_str() );
2512  }
2513  for( const migration::content &c : m.contents ) {
2514  if( !m_templates.count( c.id ) ) {
2515  debugmsg( "Invalid migration contents: %s", c.id.str() );
2516  }
2517  }
2518  }
2519  }
2520  for( const auto &elem : m_template_groups ) {
2521  elem.second->check_consistency( true );
2522  inp_mngr.pump_events();
2523  }
2524 }
2525 
2526 //Returns the template with the given identification tag
2527 const itype *Item_factory::find_template( const itype_id &id ) const
2528 {
2529  cata_assert( frozen );
2530 
2531  auto found = m_templates.find( id );
2532  if( found != m_templates.end() ) {
2533  return &found->second;
2534  }
2535 
2536  auto rt = m_runtimes.find( id );
2537  if( rt != m_runtimes.end() ) {
2538  return rt->second.get();
2539  }
2540 
2541  //If we didn't find the item maybe it is a building instead!
2542  const recipe_id &making_id = recipe_id( id.c_str() );
2543  if( oter_str_id( id.c_str() ).is_valid() ||
2544  ( making_id.is_valid() && making_id.obj().is_blueprint() ) ) {
2545  itype *def = new itype();
2546  def->id = id;
2547  def->name = no_translation( string_format( "DEBUG: %s", id.c_str() ) );
2548  def->description = making_id.obj().description;
2549  m_runtimes[ id ].reset( def );
2550  return def;
2551  }
2552 
2553  debugmsg( "Missing item definition: %s", id.c_str() );
2554 
2555  itype *def = new itype();
2556  def->id = id;
2557  def->name = no_translation( string_format( "undefined-%s", id.c_str() ) );
2558  def->description = no_translation( string_format( "Missing item definition for %s.", id.c_str() ) );
2559 
2560  m_runtimes[ id ].reset( def );
2561  return def;
2562 }
2563 
2564 Item_spawn_data *Item_factory::get_group( const item_group_id &group_tag )
2565 {
2566  GroupMap::iterator group_iter = m_template_groups.find( group_tag );
2567  if( group_iter != m_template_groups.end() ) {
2568  return group_iter->second.get();
2569  }
2570  return nullptr;
2571 }

2577 template<typename SlotType>
2578 void Item_factory::load_slot( cata::value_ptr<SlotType> &slotptr, const JsonObject &jo,
2579  const std::string &src )
2580 {
2581  if( !slotptr ) {
2582  slotptr = cata::make_value<SlotType>();

2585 }

2587 template<typename SlotType>
2588 void Item_factory::load_slot_optional( cata::value_ptr<SlotType> &slotptr, const JsonObject &jo,
2589  const std::string_view member, const std::string &src )
2590 {
2591  if( !jo.has_member( member ) ) {
2592  return;
2593  }
2594  JsonObject slotjo = jo.get_object( member );
2595  load_slot( slotptr, slotjo, src );
2596 }
2597 
2598 bool Item_factory::load_definition( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &src, itype &def )
2599 {
2600  cata_assert( !frozen );
2601 
2602  if( !jo.has_string( "copy-from" ) ) {
2603  // if this is a new definition ensure we start with a clean itype
2604  def = itype();
2605  return true;
2606  }
2607 
2608  itype_id copy_from;
2609  jo.read( "copy-from", copy_from, true );
2610  auto base = m_templates.find( copy_from );
2611  if( base != m_templates.end() ) {
2612  def = base->second;
2613  def.looks_like = copy_from;
2614  def.was_loaded = true;
2615  return true;
2616  }
2617 
2618  auto abstract = m_abstracts.find( copy_from );
2619  if( abstract != m_abstracts.end() ) {
2620  def = abstract->second;
2621  if( def.looks_like.is_empty() ) {
2622  def.looks_like = copy_from;
2623  }
2624  def.was_loaded = true;
2625  return true;
2626  }
2627 
2628  deferred.emplace_back( jo, src );
2629  jo.allow_omitted_members();
2630  return false;
2631 }
2632 
2633 void islot_milling::load( const JsonObject &jo )
2634 {
2635  optional( jo, was_loaded, "into", into_ );
2636  optional( jo, was_loaded, "recipe", recipe_ );
2637 }
2638 
2639 void islot_milling::deserialize( const JsonObject &jo )
2640 {
2641  load( jo );

2946  }

2985 template<typename T>
2986 static void apply_optional( T &value, const std::optional<T> &applied )
2987 {
2988  if( applied ) {
2989  value = *applied;
2990  }
2991 }
2992 
2993 // Gets around the issue that std::optional doesn't support
2994 // the *= and += operators required for "proportional" and "relative".
2995 template<typename T>
2996 static void get_optional( const JsonObject &jo, bool was_loaded, const std::string &member,
2997  std::optional<T> &value )
2998 {
2999  T tmp;
3000  if( value ) {
3001  tmp = *value;
3002  }
3003  optional( jo, was_loaded, member, tmp );
3004  if( jo.has_member( member ) ) {
3005  value = tmp;
3006  }
3007 }
3008 
3009 template<typename T>
3010 static void get_relative( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string_view member,
3011  std::optional<T> &value,
3012  T default_val )
3013 {
3014  if( jo.has_member( member ) ) {
3015  value = static_cast<T>( value.value_or( default_val ) + jo.get_float( member ) );
3016  }
3017 }
3018 
3019 template<typename T>
3020 static void get_proportional( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string_view member,
3021  std::optional<T> &value, T default_val )
3022 {
3023  if( jo.has_member( member ) ) {
3024  value = static_cast<T>( value.value_or( default_val ) * jo.get_float( member ) );
3025  }
3026 }
3027 
3028 void islot_armor::load( const JsonObject &jo )
3029 {
3030  optional( jo, was_loaded, "armor", sub_data );
3031 
3032  std::optional<body_part_set> covers;
3033 
3034  assign_coverage_from_json( jo, "covers", covers );
3035  get_optional( jo, was_loaded, "material_thickness", _material_thickness );
3036  get_optional( jo, was_loaded, "environmental_protection", _env_resist );
3037  get_optional( jo, was_loaded, "environmental_protection_with_filter", _env_resist_w_filter );
3038 
3039  JsonObject relative = jo.get_object( "relative" );
3040  relative.allow_omitted_members();
3041  get_relative( relative, "material_thickness", _material_thickness, 0.f );
3042  get_relative( relative, "environmental_protection", _env_resist, 0 );
3043  get_relative( relative, "environmental_protection_with_filter", _env_resist_w_filter, 0 );
3044  float _rel_encumb = 0.0f;
3045  if( relative.has_float( "encumbrance" ) ) {
3046  _rel_encumb = relative.get_float( "encumbrance" );
3047  }
3048 
3049  JsonObject proportional = jo.get_object( "proportional" );
3050  proportional.allow_omitted_members();
3051  get_proportional( proportional, "material_thickness", _material_thickness, 0.f );
3052  get_proportional( proportional, "environmental_protection", _env_resist, 0 );
3053  get_proportional( proportional, "environmental_protection_with_filter", _env_resist_w_filter, 0 );
3054  float _prop_encumb = 1.0f;
3055  if( proportional.has_float( "encumbrance" ) ) {
3056  _prop_encumb = proportional.get_float( "encumbrance" );
3057  }
3058 
3059  for( armor_portion_data &armor : sub_data ) {
3060  apply_optional( armor.avg_thickness, _material_thickness );
3061  apply_optional( armor.env_resist, _env_resist );
3062  apply_optional( armor.env_resist_w_filter, _env_resist_w_filter );
3063  if( covers ) {
3064  armor.covers = covers;
3065  }
3066 
3067  // pass down relative and proportional encumbrance
3068  if( armor.encumber > 0 ) {
3069  armor.encumber += _rel_encumb;
3070  armor.encumber *= _prop_encumb;
3071 
3072  armor.encumber = std::max( 0, armor.encumber );
3073  }
3074 
3075  if( armor.max_encumber > 0 ) {
3076  armor.max_encumber += _rel_encumb;
3077  armor.max_encumber *= _prop_encumb;
3078 
3079  armor.max_encumber = std::max( 0, armor.max_encumber );
3080  }
3081 
3082  }
3083 
3084  optional( jo, was_loaded, "sided", sided, false );
3085 
3086  optional( jo, was_loaded, "warmth", warmth, 0 );
3087  optional( jo, was_loaded, "non_functional", non_functional, itype_id() );
3088  optional( jo, was_loaded, "damage_verb", damage_verb );
3089  optional( jo, was_loaded, "power_armor", power_armor, false );
3090  optional( jo, was_loaded, "valid_mods", valid_mods );
3091 }

3094 {
3095  load( jo );
3096 }

3174  } else if( jo.has_string( "ammo_modifier" ) ) {
3175  slot.ammo_modifier.insert( ammotype( jo.get_string( "ammo_modifier" ) ) );
3176  }
3177  assign( jo, "capacity_multiplier", slot.capacity_multiplier, strict );
3178 
3179  if( jo.has_member( "acceptable_ammo" ) ) {
3180  slot.acceptable_ammo.clear();
3181  for( const std::string &e : jo.get_tags( "acceptable_ammo" ) ) {
3182  slot.acceptable_ammo.insert( ammotype( e ) );
3183  }
3184  }
3185 
3186  JsonArray mags = jo.get_array( "magazine_adaptor" );
3187  if( !mags.empty() ) {
3188  slot.magazine_adaptor.clear();
3189  }
3190  for( JsonArray arr : mags ) {
3191  ammotype ammo( arr.get_string( 0 ) ); // an ammo type (e.g. 9mm)
3192  // compatible magazines for this ammo type
3193  for( const std::string line : arr.get_array( 1 ) ) {
3194  slot.magazine_adaptor[ ammo ].insert( itype_id( line ) );
3195  }
3196  }
3197 
3198  JsonArray pockets = jo.get_array( "pocket_mods" );
3199  if( !pockets.empty() ) {
3200  optional( jo, false, "pocket_mods", slot.add_pockets );
3201  }
3202 }

3275 void Item_factory::load( islot_comestible &slot, const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &src )
3276 {
3277  bool strict = src == "dda";
3278 
3279  JsonObject relative = jo.get_object( "relative" );
3280  JsonObject proportional = jo.get_object( "proportional" );
3281  relative.allow_omitted_members();
3282  proportional.allow_omitted_members();
3283 
3284  // !slot.comesttype.empty() for was_loaded - we don't have a proper was_loaded, but
3285  // if it's been loaded before, this should have a value. If it's not, we'll catch it later.
3286  mandatory( jo, !slot.comesttype.empty(), "comestible_type", slot.comesttype );
3287  assign( jo, "tool", slot.tool, strict );
3288  assign( jo, "charges", slot.def_charges, strict, 1 );
3289  assign( jo, "quench", slot.quench, strict );
3290  assign( jo, "fun", slot.fun, strict );
3291  assign( jo, "stim", slot.stim, strict );
3292  assign( jo, "sleepiness_mod", slot.sleepiness_mod, strict );
3293  assign( jo, "healthy", slot.healthy, strict );
3294  assign( jo, "parasites", slot.parasites, strict, 0 );
3295  assign( jo, "freezing_point", slot.freeze_point, strict );
3296  assign( jo, "spoils_in", slot.spoils, strict, 1_hours );
3297  assign( jo, "cooks_like", slot.cooks_like, strict );
3298  assign( jo, "smoking_result", slot.smoking_result, strict );
3299  assign( jo, "petfood", slot.petfood, strict );
3300 
3301  for( const JsonObject jsobj : jo.get_array( "contamination" ) ) {
3302  slot.contamination.emplace( diseasetype_id( jsobj.get_string( "disease" ) ),
3303  jsobj.get_int( "probability" ) );
3304  }
3305 
3306  if( jo.has_member( "primary_material" ) ) {
3307  material_id mat( jo.get_string( "primary_material" ) );
3308  // Overwrite the materials (set by copy-from)
3309  slot.materials.clear();
3310  slot.materials.emplace( mat, 1 );
3311  } else if( jo.has_member( "material" ) ) {
3312  // Overwrite the materials (set by copy-from)
3313  slot.materials.clear();
3314 
3315  if( jo.has_array( "material" ) && jo.get_array( "material" ).test_object() ) {
3316  for( JsonObject m : jo.get_array( "material" ) ) {
3317  const material_id mat_id( m.get_string( "type" ) );
3318  int portion = m.get_int( "portion", 1 );
3319  slot.materials.emplace( mat_id, portion );
3320  }
3321  } else {
3322  for( const std::string &m : jo.get_tags( "material" ) ) {
3323  slot.materials.emplace( m, 1 );
3324  }
3325  }
3326  }
3327 
3328  assign( jo, "monotony_penalty", slot.monotony_penalty, strict );
3329  assign( jo, "addiction_potential", slot.default_addict_potential, strict );
3330  if( jo.has_member( "addiction_type" ) ) {
3331  slot.addictions.clear();
3332  if( jo.has_string( "addiction_type" ) ) {
3333  slot.addictions.emplace( addiction_id( jo.get_string( "addiction_type" ) ),
3334  slot.default_addict_potential );
3335  } else { //"addiction_type" is an array
3336  for( JsonValue jval : jo.get_array( "addiction_type" ) ) {
3337  if( jval.test_string() ) {
3338  slot.addictions.emplace( addiction_id( jval.get_string() ), slot.default_addict_potential );
3339  } else { //nested object with addiction + potential
3340  JsonObject jobj = jval.get_object();
3341  slot.addictions.emplace( addiction_id( jobj.get_string( "addiction" ) ),
3342  jobj.get_int( "potential" ) );
3343  }
3344  }
3345  }
3346  } else if( jo.has_member( "addiction_potential" ) ) {
3347  // copy-from'd while only changing the general potential, so assign new potential to all addictions
3348  for( std::pair<const addiction_id, int> &add : slot.addictions ) {
3349  add.second = slot.default_addict_potential;
3350  }
3351  }
3352 
3353  bool got_calories = false;
3354 
3355  if( jo.has_member( "calories" ) ) {
3356  // The value here is in kcal, but is stored as simply calories
3357  slot.default_nutrition.calories = 1000 * jo.get_int( "calories" );
3358  got_calories = true;
3359 
3360  } else if( relative.has_member( "calories" ) ) {
3361  // The value here is in kcal, but is stored as simply calories
3362  slot.default_nutrition.calories += 1000 * relative.get_int( "calories" );
3363  got_calories = true;
3364 
3365  } else if( proportional.has_member( "calories" ) ) {
3366  // The value here is in kcal, but is stored as simply calories
3367  slot.default_nutrition.calories *= proportional.get_float( "calories" );
3368  got_calories = true;
3369 
3370  } else if( jo.has_member( "nutrition" ) ) {
3371  // The value here is in kcal, but is stored as simply calories
3372  slot.default_nutrition.calories = jo.get_int( "nutrition" ) * islot_comestible::kcal_per_nutr *
3373  1000;
3374  }
3375 
3376  for( JsonValue jv : jo.get_array( "consumption_effect_on_conditions" ) ) {
3377  slot.consumption_eocs.push_back( effect_on_conditions::load_inline_eoc( jv, src ) );
3378  }
3379 
3380  if( jo.has_member( "nutrition" ) && got_calories ) {
3381  jo.throw_error_at( "nutrition", "cannot specify both nutrition and calories" );
3382  }
3383 
3384  // any specification of vitamins suppresses use of material defaults @see Item_factory::finalize
3385  if( jo.has_array( "vitamins" ) ) {
3386  slot.default_nutrition.finalized = false;
3387  for( JsonArray pair : jo.get_array( "vitamins" ) ) {
3388  vitamin_id vit( pair.get_string( 0 ) );
3389  if( pair.has_int( 1 ) ) {
3390  slot.default_nutrition.set_vitamin( vit, pair.get_int( 1 ) );
3391  } else {
3392  vitamin_units::mass val = read_from_json_string( pair[1], vitamin_units::mass_units );
3393  slot.default_nutrition.set_vitamin( vit, val );
3394  }
3395  }
3396 
3397  } else if( relative.has_array( "vitamins" ) ) {
3398  for( JsonArray pair : relative.get_array( "vitamins" ) ) {
3399  vitamin_id vit( pair.get_string( 0 ) );
3400  if( pair.has_int( 1 ) ) {
3401  slot.default_nutrition.add_vitamin( vit, pair.get_int( 1 ) );
3402  } else {
3403  vitamin_units::mass val = read_from_json_string( pair[1], vitamin_units::mass_units );
3404  slot.default_nutrition.add_vitamin( vit, val );
3405  }
3406  }
3407  }
3408 
3409  if( jo.has_string( "rot_spawn" ) ) {
3410  slot.rot_spawn = mongroup_id( jo.get_string( "rot_spawn" ) );
3411  }
3412  assign( jo, "rot_spawn_chance", slot.rot_spawn_chance, strict, 0 );
3413 
3414 }

3641 // Adds allergy flags to items with allergenic materials
3642 // Set for all items (not just food and clothing) to avoid edge cases
3643 void Item_factory::set_allergy_flags( itype &item_template )
3644 {
3645  static const std::array<std::pair<material_id, flag_id>, 29> all_pairs = { {
3646  // First allergens:
3647  // An item is an allergen even if it has trace amounts of allergenic material
3648  { material_hflesh, flag_ALLERGEN_MEAT },
3649  { material_iflesh, flag_ALLERGEN_MEAT },
3650  { material_bread, flag_ALLERGEN_BREAD },
3651  { material_flesh, flag_ALLERGEN_MEAT },
3652  { material_cheese, flag_ALLERGEN_CHEESE},
3653  { material_blood, flag_ALLERGEN_MEAT },
3654  { material_hblood, flag_ALLERGEN_MEAT },
3655  { material_bone, flag_ALLERGEN_MEAT },
3656  { material_wheat, flag_ALLERGEN_WHEAT },
3657  { material_fruit, flag_ALLERGEN_FRUIT },
3658  { material_veggy, flag_ALLERGEN_VEGGY },
3659  { material_dried_vegetable, flag_ALLERGEN_DRIED_VEGETABLE },
3660  { material_bean, flag_ALLERGEN_VEGGY },
3661  { material_tomato, flag_ALLERGEN_VEGGY },
3662  { material_garlic, flag_ALLERGEN_VEGGY },
3663  { material_nut, flag_ALLERGEN_NUT },
3664  { material_mushroom, flag_ALLERGEN_VEGGY },
3665  { material_milk, flag_ALLERGEN_MILK },
3666  { material_egg, flag_ALLERGEN_EGG },
3667  { material_junk, flag_ALLERGEN_JUNK },
3668  // Not food, but we can keep it here
3669  { material_wool, flag_ALLERGEN_WOOL },
3670  // Now "made of". Those flags should not be passed
3671  { material_flesh, flag_CARNIVORE_OK },
3672  { material_hflesh, flag_CARNIVORE_OK },
3673  { material_iflesh, flag_CARNIVORE_OK },
3674  { material_blood, flag_CARNIVORE_OK },
3675  { material_hblood, flag_CARNIVORE_OK },
3676  { material_honey, flag_URSINE_HONEY },
3677  { material_blood, flag_HEMOVORE_FUN },
3678  { material_hblood, flag_HEMOVORE_FUN }
3679  }
3680  };
3681 
3682  const auto &mats = item_template.materials;
3683  for( const auto &pr : all_pairs ) {
3684  if( mats.find( pr.first ) != mats.end() ) {
3685  item_template.item_tags.insert( pr.second );
3686  }
3687  }
3688 }

3690 // Migration helper: turns human flesh into generic flesh
3691 // Don't call before making sure that the cannibalism flag is set
3692 // Cannibalism is vitamin based now but how old is this? Is it still useful?
3693 void hflesh_to_flesh( itype &item_template )
3694 {
3695  auto &mats = item_template.materials;
3696  const size_t old_size = mats.size();
3697  int ports = 0;
3698  for( auto mat = mats.begin(); mat != mats.end(); ) {
3699  if( mat->first == material_hflesh ) {
3700  ports += mat->second;
3701  mat = mats.erase( mat );
3702  } else {
3703  mat++;
3704  }
3705  }
3706  // Only add "flesh" material if not already present
3707  if( old_size != mats.size() &&
3708  mats.find( material_flesh ) == mats.end() ) {
3709  mats.emplace( "flesh", ports );
3710  }
3711 }

3713 void Item_factory::npc_implied_flags( itype &item_template )
3714 {
3715  if( item_template.use_methods.count( "explosion" ) > 0 ) {
3716  item_template.item_tags.insert( flag_DANGEROUS );
3717  }
3718 
3719  if( item_template.has_flag( flag_DANGEROUS ) ) {
3720  item_template.item_tags.insert( flag_NPC_THROW_NOW );
3721  }
3722 
3723  if( item_template.has_flag( flag_BOMB ) ) {
3724  item_template.item_tags.insert( flag_NPC_ACTIVATE );
3725  }
3726 
3727  if( item_template.has_flag( flag_NPC_THROW_NOW ) ) {
3728  item_template.item_tags.insert( flag_NPC_THROWN );
3729  }
3730 
3731  if( item_template.has_flag( flag_NPC_ACTIVATE ) ||
3732  item_template.has_flag( flag_NPC_THROWN ) ) {
3733  item_template.item_tags.insert( flag_NPC_ALT_ATTACK );
3734  }
3735 
3736  if( item_template.has_flag( flag_DANGEROUS ) ||
3737  item_template.has_flag( flag_PSEUDO ) || item_template.has_flag( flag_INTEGRATED ) ) {
3738  item_template.item_tags.insert( flag_TRADER_AVOID );

3742 static bool has_pocket_type( const std::vector<pocket_data> &data, pocket_type pk )
3743 {
3744  for( const pocket_data &pocket : data ) {
3745  if( pocket.type == pk ) {
3746  return true;
3747  }
3748  }
3749  return false;
3750 }
3751 
3752 static bool has_only_special_pockets( const itype &def )
3753 {
3754  // There are some places where we need to know whether any non-special
3755  // pockets have been added. There might be no pockets, or there might be
3756  // just the special ones, depending on whether the definition is
3757  // copied-from another or not.
3758  if( def.pockets.empty() ) {
3759  return true;
3760  }
3761 
3762  const std::vector<pocket_type> special_pockets = { pocket_type::CORPSE, pocket_type::MOD, pocket_type::MIGRATION };
3763 
3764  for( const pocket_data &pocket : def.pockets ) {
3765  if( std::find( special_pockets.begin(), special_pockets.end(),
3766  pocket.type ) == special_pockets.end() ) {
3767  return false;
3768  }
3769  }
3770 
3771  return true;
3772 }
3773 
3774 void Item_factory::check_and_create_magazine_pockets( itype &def )
3775 {
3776  // the item we're trying to migrate must actually have data for ammo
3777  if( def.magazines.empty() && !( def.magazine || def.tool ) ) {
3778  return;
3779  }
3780  if( def.tool && def.tool->ammo_id.empty() ) {
3781  // If tool has no ammo type it needs no magazine.
3782  return;
3783  }
3784  if( def.tool && def.tool->max_charges == 0 && def.magazines.empty() ) {
3785  // If tool has no charges nor magazines, it needs no magazine.
3786  return;
3787  }
3788  if( !has_only_special_pockets( def ) ) {
3789  // this means pockets were defined in json already
3790  // we assume they're good to go, or error elsewhere
3791  if( def.tool && def.tool->max_charges != 0 ) {
3792  // warn about redundant max_charges definition
3793  debugmsg( "Redundant max charge value specified for %s with magazine pocket.",
3794  def.get_id().str() );
3795  }
3796  return;
3797  }
3798 
3799  // Thing uses no ammo
3800  if( def.magazine && def.magazine->type.empty() ) {
3801  return;
3802  }
3803  if( def.tool && def.tool->ammo_id.empty() ) {
3804  return;
3805  }
3806 
3807  pocket_data mag_data;
3808  mag_data.holster = true;
3809  mag_data.volume_capacity = 200_liter;
3810  mag_data.max_contains_weight = 2000000_kilogram;
3811  mag_data.max_item_length = 2_km;
3812  mag_data.watertight = true;
3813  if( !def.magazines.empty() ) {
3814  mag_data.type = pocket_type::MAGAZINE_WELL;
3815  mag_data.rigid = false;
3816  ammotype default_ammo = ammotype::NULL_ID();
3817  if( def.tool ) {
3818  default_ammo = *def.tool->ammo_id.begin();
3819  }
3820  if( !default_ammo.is_null() ) {
3821  auto magazines_for_default_ammo = def.magazines.find( default_ammo );
3822  if( magazines_for_default_ammo == def.magazines.end() ) {
3823  debugmsg( "item %s defines magazines but no magazine for its default ammo type",
3824  def.get_id().str() );
3825  } else {
3826  cata_assert( !magazines_for_default_ammo->second.empty() );
3827  mag_data.default_magazine = *magazines_for_default_ammo->second.begin();
3828  }
3829  }
3830  for( const std::pair<const ammotype, std::set<itype_id>> &mag_pair : def.magazines ) {
3831  for( const itype_id &mag_type : mag_pair.second ) {
3832  mag_data.item_id_restriction.insert( mag_type );
3833  }
3834  }
3835  } else {
3836  mag_data.type = pocket_type::MAGAZINE;
3837  mag_data.rigid = true;
3838  if( def.magazine ) {
3839  for( const ammotype &amtype : def.magazine->type ) {
3840  mag_data.ammo_restriction.emplace( amtype, def.magazine->capacity );
3841  }
3842  }
3843  if( def.tool ) {
3844  for( const ammotype &amtype : def.tool->ammo_id ) {
3845  mag_data.ammo_restriction.emplace( amtype, def.tool->max_charges );
3846  }
3847  def.tool->max_charges = 0;
3848  def.tool->def_charges = 0;
3849  }
3850  }
3851  def.pockets.push_back( mag_data );
3852  debugmsg( _( "%s needs pocket definitions" ), def.get_id().str() );
3853 }
3854 
3855 void Item_factory::add_special_pockets( itype &def )
3856 {
3857  if( def.has_flag( flag_CORPSE ) &&
3858  !has_pocket_type( def.pockets, pocket_type::CORPSE ) ) {
3859  def.pockets.emplace_back( pocket_type::CORPSE );
3860  }
3861  if( ( def.tool || def.gun ) && !has_pocket_type( def.pockets, pocket_type::MOD ) ) {
3862  def.pockets.emplace_back( pocket_type::MOD );
3863  }
3864  if( !has_pocket_type( def.pockets, pocket_type::MIGRATION ) ) {
3865  def.pockets.emplace_back( pocket_type::MIGRATION );
3866  }
3867  if( !has_pocket_type( def.pockets, pocket_type::CABLE ) &&
3868  def.get_use( "link_up" ) != nullptr ) {
3869  pocket_data cable_pocket( pocket_type::CABLE );
3870  cable_pocket.rigid = false;
3871  def.pockets.emplace_back( cable_pocket );
3872  }
3873 }

4027 struct acc_data {
4028  grip_val grip = grip_val::WEAPON;
4029  length_val length = length_val::HAND;
4030  surface_val surface = surface_val::ANY;
4031  balance_val balance = balance_val::NEUTRAL;
4032 
4033  // all items have a basic accuracy of -2, per GAME_BALANCE.md
4034  static constexpr int base_acc = -2;
4035  // grip val should go from -1 to 2 but enum_to_string wants to start at 0
4036  static constexpr int grip_offset = -1;
4037  // surface val should from from -2 to 1 but enum_to_string wants to start at 0
4038  static constexpr int surface_offset = -2;
4039  // balance val should from from -2 to 1 but enum_to_string wants to start at 0
4040  static constexpr int balance_offset = -2;
4041  // all the constant offsets and the base accuracy together
4042  static constexpr int acc_offset = base_acc + grip_offset + surface_offset + balance_offset;
4043  int sum_values() const {
4044  return acc_offset + static_cast<int>( grip ) + static_cast<int>( length ) +
4045  static_cast<int>( surface ) + static_cast<int>( balance );
4046  }
4047  void deserialize(const JsonObject& jo);
4048  void load( const JsonObject &jo );
4049 };
4050 
4051 void acc_data::deserialize( const JsonObject& jo )
4052 {
4053  load( jo );
4054 }
4055 
4056 void acc_data::load( const JsonObject &jo )
4057 {
4058  bool was_loaded = false;
4059  optional( jo, was_loaded, "grip", grip, grip_val::WEAPON );
4060  optional( jo, was_loaded, "length", length, length_val::HAND );
4061  optional( jo, was_loaded, "surface", surface, surface_val::ANY );
4062  optional( jo, was_loaded, "balance", balance, balance_val::NEUTRAL );
4063 }
4064 // *INDENT-ON*
4065 } // namespace io

4067 static void migrate_mag_from_pockets( itype &def )
4068 {
4069  for( const pocket_data &pocket : def.pockets ) {
4070  if( pocket.type == pocket_type::MAGAZINE_WELL ) {
4071  if( def.gun ) {
4072  for( const ammotype &atype : def.gun->ammo ) {
4073  def.magazine_default.emplace( atype, pocket.default_magazine );
4074  }
4075  }
4076  if( def.magazine ) {
4077  for( const ammotype &atype : def.magazine->type ) {
4078  def.magazine_default.emplace( atype, pocket.default_magazine );
4079  }
4080  }
4081  if( def.tool ) {
4082  for( const ammotype &atype : def.tool->ammo_id ) {
4083  def.magazine_default.emplace( atype, pocket.default_magazine );
4084  }
4085  }
4086  }
4087  }
4088 }

4090 static void replace_materials( const JsonObject &jo, itype &def )
4091 {
4092  // itterate through material replacements
4093  for( JsonMember jv : jo ) {
4094  material_id to_replace = material_id( jv.name() );
4095  material_id replacement = material_id( jv.get_string() );
4096 
4097  units::mass original_weight = def.weight;
4098  int mat_portion = def.materials[to_replace];
4099 
4100  // make repairs_with act the same way
4101  if( !def.repairs_with.empty() ) {
4102  const auto iter = def.repairs_with.find( to_replace );
4103  if( iter != def.repairs_with.end() ) {
4104  def.repairs_with.erase( iter );
4105  def.repairs_with.insert( replacement );
4106  }
4107  }
4108 
4109  // material is defined
4110  if( mat_portion != 0 ) {
4111  double mat_percent = static_cast<double>( mat_portion ) / static_cast<double>
4112  ( def.mat_portion_total );
4113 
4114  float density_percent = replacement->density() / to_replace->density();
4115 
4116  // add the portion for the replaced material
4117  def.materials[replacement] += mat_portion;
4118 
4119  // delete the old data
4120  def.materials.erase( to_replace );
4121 
4122  // change the weight relative
4123  units::mass material_weight = original_weight * mat_percent;
4124  units::mass weight_dif = material_weight * density_percent - material_weight;
4125 
4126  def.weight += weight_dif;
4127  }
4128 
4129  // update the armor defs
4130  if( def.armor ) {
4131  for( armor_portion_data &data : def.armor->sub_data ) {
4132  std::vector<part_material>::iterator entry;
4133  do {
4134  entry = std::find_if( data.materials.begin(),
4135  data.materials.end(), [to_replace]( const part_material & pm ) {
4136  return pm.id == to_replace;
4137  } );
4138 
4139  if( entry != data.materials.end() ) {
4140  entry->id = replacement;
4141  }
4142 
4143  } while( entry != data.materials.end() );
4144  }
4145  }
4146  }
4147 }

4149 void Item_factory::load_basic_info( const JsonObject &jo, itype &def, const std::string &src )
4150 {
4151  bool strict = src == "dda";
4152 
4153  restore_on_out_of_scope<check_plural_t> restore_check_plural( check_plural );
4154  if( jo.has_string( "abstract" ) ) {
4155  check_plural = check_plural_t::none;
4156  }
4157 
4158  assign( jo, "category", def.category_force, strict );
4159  assign( jo, "weight", def.weight, strict, 0_gram );
4160  assign( jo, "integral_weight", def.integral_weight, strict, 0_gram );
4161  assign( jo, "volume", def.volume );
4162  assign( jo, "longest_side", def.longest_side );
4163  assign( jo, "price", def.price, false, 0_cent );
4164  assign( jo, "price_postapoc", def.price_post, false, 0_cent );
4165  assign( jo, "stackable", def.stackable_, strict );
4166  assign( jo, "integral_volume", def.integral_volume );
4167  assign( jo, "integral_longest_side", def.integral_longest_side, false, 0_mm );
4168  if( jo.has_object( "melee_damage" ) ) {
4169  def.melee = load_damage_map( jo.get_object( "melee_damage" ) );
4170  }
4171  def.melee_proportional.clear();
4172  if( jo.has_object( "proportional" ) ) {
4173  JsonObject jprop = jo.get_object( "proportional" );
4174  jprop.allow_omitted_members();
4175  if( jprop.has_object( "melee_damage" ) ) {
4176  def.melee_proportional = load_damage_map( jprop.get_object( "melee_damage" ) );
4177  }
4178  }
4179  def.melee_relative.clear();
4180  if( jo.has_object( "relative" ) ) {
4181  JsonObject jrel = jo.get_object( "relative" );
4182  jrel.allow_omitted_members();
4183  if( jrel.has_object( "melee_damage" ) ) {
4184  def.melee_relative = load_damage_map( jrel.get_object( "melee_damage" ) );
4185  }
4186  }
4187  if( jo.has_int( "to_hit" ) ) {
4188  assign( jo, "to_hit", def.m_to_hit, strict );
4189  } else if( jo.has_object( "to_hit" ) ) {
4190  io::acc_data temp;
4191  bool was_loaded = false;
4192  mandatory( jo, was_loaded, "to_hit", temp );
4193  def.m_to_hit = temp.sum_values();
4194  }
4195  optional( jo, false, "variant_type", def.variant_kind, itype_variant_kind::generic );
4196  optional( jo, false, "variants", def.variants );
4197  assign( jo, "container", def.default_container );
4198  optional( jo, false, "container_variant", def.default_container_variant );
4199  assign( jo, "sealed", def.default_container_sealed );
4200  assign( jo, "min_strength", def.min_str );
4201  assign( jo, "min_dexterity", def.min_dex );
4202  assign( jo, "min_intelligence", def.min_int );
4203  assign( jo, "min_perception", def.min_per );
4204  assign( jo, "emits", def.emits );
4205  assign( jo, "explode_in_fire", def.explode_in_fire );
4206  assign( jo, "insulation", def.insulation_factor );
4207  assign( jo, "solar_efficiency", def.solar_efficiency );
4208  assign( jo, "ascii_picture", def.picture_id );
4209  assign( jo, "repairs_with", def.repairs_with );
4210 
4211  if( jo.has_member( "thrown_damage" ) ) {
4212  def.thrown_damage = load_damage_instance( jo.get_array( "thrown_damage" ) );
4213  } else {
4214  // TODO: Move to finalization
4215  def.thrown_damage.clear();
4216  def.thrown_damage.add_damage( damage_bash,
4217  def.melee[damage_bash] + def.weight / 1.0_kilogram );
4218  }
4219 
4220  if( jo.has_member( "repairs_like" ) ) {
4221  jo.read( "repairs_like", def.repairs_like );
4222  }
4223 
4224  optional( jo, true, "weapon_category", def.weapon_category, auto_flags_reader<weapon_category_id> {} );
4225 
4226  float degrade_mult = 1.0f;
4227  optional( jo, false, "degradation_multiplier", degrade_mult, 1.0f );
4228  // TODO: remove condition once degradation is ready to be applied to all items
4229  if( def.count_by_charges() || def.category_force != item_category_veh_parts ) {
4230  degrade_mult = 0.0f;
4231  }
4232  if( ( degrade_mult * itype::damage_max_ ) <= 0.5f ) {
4233  def.degrade_increments_ = 0;
4234  } else {
4235  float adjusted_inc = std::max( def.degrade_increments_ / degrade_mult, 1.0f );
4236  def.degrade_increments_ = std::isnan( adjusted_inc ) ? 0 : std::round( adjusted_inc );
4237  }
4238 
4239  def.name = translation( translation::plural_tag() );
4240  if( !jo.read( "name", def.name ) ) {
4241  jo.throw_error( "name unspecified for item type" );
4242  }
4243 
4244  if( jo.has_member( "description" ) ) {
4245  jo.read( "description", def.description );
4246  }
4247 
4248  if( jo.has_string( "symbol" ) ) {
4249  def.sym = jo.get_string( "symbol" );
4250  }
4251 
4252  if( jo.has_string( "color" ) ) {
4253  def.color = color_from_string( jo.get_string( "color" ) );
4254  }
4255 
4256  if( jo.has_member( "material" ) ) {
4257  def.materials.clear();
4258  def.mat_portion_total = 0;
4259  auto add_mat = [&def]( const material_id & m, int portion ) {
4260  const auto res = def.materials.emplace( m, portion );
4261  if( res.second ) {
4262  def.mat_portion_total += portion;
4263  }
4264  };
4265  bool first = true;

4515 void Item_factory::add_migration( const migration &m )
4516 {
4517  auto it = migrations.find( m.id );
4518  if( it == migrations.end() ) {
4519  migrations[m.id] = {m};
4520  return;
4521  }
4522 
4523  for( migration &old : it->second ) {
4524  if( old.from_variant ) {
4525  continue;
4526  }
4527  // If we find one that isn't from variant, overwrite it
4528  old = m;
4529  return;
4530  }
4531 
4532  // Otherwise, we're specifying a new one.
4533  it->second.push_back( m );
4534 }
4535 
4536 void Item_factory::load_migration( const JsonObject &jo )
4537 {
4538  migration m;
4539  assign( jo, "replace", m.replace );
4540  assign( jo, "variant", m.variant );
4541  assign( jo, "from_variant", m.from_variant );
4542  assign( jo, "flags", m.flags );
4543  assign( jo, "charges", m.charges );
4544  assign( jo, "contents", m.contents );
4545  assign( jo, "sealed", m.sealed );
4546  assign( jo, "reset_item_vars", m.reset_item_vars );
4547 
4548  std::vector<itype_id> ids;
4549  if( jo.has_string( "id" ) ) {
4550  ids.resize( 1 );
4551  jo.read( "id", ids[0], true );
4552  } else if( jo.has_array( "id" ) ) {
4553  jo.read( "id", ids, true );
4554  } else {
4555  jo.throw_error( "`id` of `MIGRATION` is neither string nor array" );
4556  }
4557  for( const itype_id &id : ids ) {
4558  if( m.replace && m.replace == id ) {
4559  jo.throw_error( string_format( "`MIGRATION` attempting to replace entity with itself: %s",
4560  id.str() ) );
4561  }
4562  m.id = id;
4563  if( m.from_variant ) {
4564  migrations[ m.id ].push_back( m );
4565  } else {
4566  add_migration( m );
4567  }
4568  }
4569 }
4570 
4571 bool migration::content::operator==( const content &rhs ) const
4572 {
4573  return id == rhs.id && count == rhs.count;
4574 }
4575 
4576 void migration::content::deserialize( const JsonObject &jsobj )
4577 {
4578  jsobj.get_member( "id" ).read( id );
4579  jsobj.get_member( "count" ).read( count );
4580 }
4581 
4582 itype_id Item_factory::migrate_id( const itype_id &id )
4583 {
4584  auto iter = migrations.find( id );
4585  if( iter == migrations.end() ) {
4586  return id;
4587  }
4588  const migration *parent = nullptr;
4589  for( const migration &m : iter->second ) {
4590  // from-variant migrations do not apply to itypes
4591  if( m.from_variant ) {
4592  continue;
4593  }
4594  parent = &m;
4595  break;
4596  }
4597  return parent != nullptr ? parent->replace : id;
4598 }
4599 
4600 static void apply_migration( const migration *migrant, item &obj )
4601 {
4602  if( migrant->reset_item_vars ) {
4603  obj.clear_vars();
4604  for( const auto &pair : migrant->replace.obj().item_variables ) {
4605  obj.set_var( pair.first, pair.second ) ;
4606  }
4607  }
4608  for( const std::string &f : migrant->flags ) {
4609  obj.set_flag( flag_id( f ) );
4610  }
4611  if( migrant->charges > 0 ) {
4612  obj.charges = migrant->charges;
4613  }
4614 
4615  if( migrant->from_variant ) {
4616  obj.clear_itype_variant();
4617  }
4618  obj.set_itype_variant( migrant->variant );
4619 
4620  for( const migration::content &it : migrant->contents ) {
4621  int count = it.count;
4622  item content( it.id, obj.birthday(), 1 );
4623  if( content.count_by_charges() ) {
4624  content.charges = count;
4625  count = 1;
4626  }
4627  for( ; count > 0; --count ) {
4628  if( !obj.put_in( content, pocket_type::CONTAINER ).success() ) {
4629  obj.put_in( content, pocket_type::MIGRATION );
4630  }
4631  }
4632  }
4633 
4634  if( !migrant->contents.empty() && migrant->sealed ) {
4635  obj.seal();
4636  }
4637 }
4638 
4639 void Item_factory::migrate_item( const itype_id &id, item &obj )
4640 {
4641  auto iter = migrations.find( id );
4642  if( iter == migrations.end() ) {
4643  return;
4644  }
4645  bool convert = false;
4646  const migration *migrant = nullptr;
4647  for( const migration &m : iter->second ) {
4648  if( m.from_variant && obj.has_itype_variant() && obj.itype_variant().id == *m.from_variant ) {
4649  migrant = &m;
4650  // This is not the variant that the item has already been convert to
4651  // So we'll convert it again.
4652  convert = true;
4653  break;
4654  }
4655  // When we find a migration that doesn't care about variants, keep it around
4656  if( !m.from_variant ) {
4657  migrant = &m;
4658  }
4659  }
4660  if( migrant == nullptr ) {
4661  return;
4662  }
4663 
4664  if( convert ) {
4665  obj.convert( migrant->replace );
4666  }
4667 
4668  apply_migration( migrant, obj );
4669 }
4670 
4671 void Item_factory::migrate_item_from_variant( item &obj, const std::string &from_variant )
4672 {
4673  auto iter = migrations.find( obj.typeId() );
4674  if( iter == migrations.end() ) {
4675  return;
4676  }
4677  for( const migration &m : iter->second ) {
4678  if( !m.from_variant.has_value() || m.from_variant.value() != from_variant ) {
4679  continue;
4680  }
4681  obj.convert( m.replace );
4682  apply_migration( &m, obj );
4683  break;
4684  }
4685 }

4687 void Item_factory::set_qualities_from_json( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &member,
4688  itype &def )
4689 {
4690  if( jo.has_array( member ) ) {
4691  for( JsonArray curr : jo.get_array( member ) ) {
4692  const auto quali = std::pair<quality_id, int>( quality_id( curr.get_string( 0 ) ),
4693  curr.get_int( 1 ) );
4694  // Populate charged qualities or regular qualities, preventing duplicates
4695  if( member == "charged_qualities" ) {
4696  if( def.charged_qualities.count( quali.first ) > 0 ) {
4697  curr.throw_error( 0, "Duplicated charged quality" );
4698  }
4699  def.charged_qualities.insert( quali );
4700  } else {
4701  if( def.qualities.count( quali.first ) > 0 ) {
4702  curr.throw_error( 0, "Duplicated quality" );
4703  }
4704  def.qualities.insert( quali );
4705  }
4706  }
4707  } else {
4708  jo.throw_error_at( member, "Qualities list is not an array" );
4709  }
4710 }
4711 
4712 void Item_factory::extend_qualities_from_json( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string_view member,
4713  itype &def )
4714 {
4715  for( JsonArray curr : jo.get_array( member ) ) {

4717  }

4720 void Item_factory::delete_qualities_from_json( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string_view member,
4721  itype &def )
4722 {
4723  for( std::string curr : jo.get_array( member ) ) {
4724  const auto iter = def.qualities.find( quality_id( curr ) );
4725  if( iter != def.qualities.end() ) {
4726  def.qualities.erase( iter );
4727  }
4728  }
4729 }

4731 void Item_factory::relative_qualities_from_json( const JsonObject &jo,
4732  const std::string_view member, itype &def )

4736  if( def.qualities.find( quality_id( key ) ) != def.qualities.end() ) {
4737  def.qualities[ key ] += curr.get_int( 1 );
4738  } else {
4739  jo.throw_error_at( member, "Quality specified wasn't inherited" );
4740  }
4741  }

4817 static std::string to_string( Item_group::Type t )
4818 {
4819  switch( t ) {
4820  case Item_group::Type::G_COLLECTION:
4821  return "collection";
4822  case Item_group::Type::G_DISTRIBUTION:
4823  return "distribution";
4824  }
4825 
4826  return "BUGGED";
4827 }
4828 
4829 static Item_group *make_group_or_throw(
4830  const item_group_id &group_id, std::unique_ptr<Item_spawn_data> &isd, Item_group::Type t,
4831  int ammo_chance, int magazine_chance, const std::string &context )
4832 {
4833  Item_group *ig = dynamic_cast<Item_group *>( isd.get() );
4834  if( ig == nullptr ) {
4835  isd.reset( ig = new Item_group( t, 100, ammo_chance, magazine_chance, context ) );
4836  } else if( ig->type != t ) {
4837  throw std::runtime_error(
4838  "item group \"" + group_id.str() + "\" already defined with type \"" +
4839  to_string( ig->type ) + "\"" );
4840  }
4841  return ig;
4842 }
4843 
4844 template<typename T>
4845 bool load_min_max( std::pair<T, T> &pa, const JsonObject &obj, const std::string &name )
4846 {
4847  bool result = false;
4848  if( obj.has_array( name ) ) {
4849  // An array means first is min, second entry is max. Both are mandatory.
4850  JsonArray arr = obj.get_array( name );
4851  result |= arr.read_next( pa.first );
4852  result |= arr.read_next( pa.second );
4853  } else {
4854  // Not an array, should be a single numeric value, which is set as min and max.
4855  result |= obj.read( name, pa.first );
4856  result |= obj.read( name, pa.second );
4857  }
4858  result |= obj.read( name + "-min", pa.first );
4859  result |= obj.read( name + "-max", pa.second );
4860  return result;
4861 }
4862 
4863 template<typename T>
4864 bool load_str_arr( std::vector<T> &arr, const JsonObject &obj, const std::string_view name )
4865 {
4866  if( obj.has_array( name ) ) {
4867  for( const std::string str : obj.get_array( name ) ) {
4868  arr.emplace_back( str );
4869  }
4870  return true;
4871  }
4872  return false;
4873 }
4874 
4875 bool Item_factory::load_sub_ref( std::unique_ptr<Item_spawn_data> &ptr, const JsonObject &obj,
4876  const std::string &name, const Item_group &parent )
4877 {
4878  const std::string iname( name + "-item" );
4879  const std::string gname( name + "-group" );
4880 
4881  // pair.second is true for groups, false for items
4882  std::vector< std::pair<std::string, bool> > entries;
4883  const int prob = 100;
4884 
4885  auto get_array = [&obj, &name, &entries]( const std::string & arr_name, const bool isgroup ) {
4886  if( !obj.has_array( arr_name ) ) {
4887  return;
4888  } else if( name != "contents" ) {
4889  obj.throw_error( string_format( "You can't use an array for '%s'", arr_name ) );
4890  }
4891  for( const std::string line : obj.get_array( arr_name ) ) {
4892  entries.emplace_back( line, isgroup );
4893  }
4894  };
4895  get_array( iname, false );
4896  get_array( gname, true );
4897 
4898  if( obj.has_member( name ) ) {
4899  obj.throw_error( string_format( "This has been a TODO: since 2014. Use '%s' and/or '%s' instead.",
4900  iname, gname ) );
4901  }
4902  if( obj.has_string( iname ) ) {
4903  entries.emplace_back( obj.get_string( iname ), false );
4904  }
4905  if( obj.has_string( gname ) ) {
4906  entries.emplace_back( obj.get_string( gname ), true );
4907  }
4908 
4909  const std::string subcontext = name + " of " + parent.context();
4910 
4911  if( entries.size() > 1 && name != "contents" ) {
4912  obj.throw_error( string_format( "You can only use one of '%s' and '%s'", iname, gname ) );
4913  } else if( entries.size() == 1 ) {
4914  const Single_item_creator::Type type = entries.front().second ?
4915  Single_item_creator::Type::S_ITEM_GROUP :
4916  Single_item_creator::Type::S_ITEM;
4917  Single_item_creator *result =
4918  new Single_item_creator( entries.front().first, type, prob, subcontext );
4919  result->inherit_ammo_mag_chances( parent.with_ammo, parent.with_magazine );
4920  ptr.reset( result );
4921  return true;
4922  } else if( entries.empty() ) {
4923  return false;
4924  }
4925  Item_group *result = new Item_group( Item_group::Type::G_COLLECTION, prob, parent.with_ammo,
4926  parent.with_magazine, subcontext );
4927  ptr.reset( result );
4928  for( const auto &elem : entries ) {
4929  if( elem.second ) {
4930  result->add_group_entry( item_group_id( elem.first ), prob );
4931  } else {
4932  result->add_item_entry( itype_id( elem.first ), prob );
4933  }
4934  }
4935  return true;
4936 }
4937 
4938 bool Item_factory::load_string( std::vector<std::string> &vec, const JsonObject &obj,
4939  const std::string_view name )
4940 {
4941  bool result = false;
4942  std::string temp;
4943 
4944  if( obj.has_array( name ) ) {
4945  for( const std::string line : obj.get_array( name ) ) {
4946  result |= true;
4947  vec.push_back( line );
4948  }
4949  } else if( obj.has_member( name ) ) {
4950  result |= obj.read( name, temp );
4951  vec.push_back( temp );
4952  }
4953 
4954  return result;
4955 }
4956 
4957 void Item_factory::add_entry( Item_group &ig, const JsonObject &obj, const std::string &context )
4958 {
4959  std::unique_ptr<Item_group> gptr;
4960  int probability = obj.get_int( "prob", 100 );
4961  holiday event = obj.get_enum_value<holiday>( "event", holiday::none );
4962  std::string subcontext = "entry within " + context;
4963  JsonArray jarr;
4964  if( obj.has_member( "collection" ) ) {
4965  gptr = std::make_unique<Item_group>( Item_group::G_COLLECTION, probability, ig.with_ammo,
4966  ig.with_magazine, context, event );
4967  jarr = obj.get_array( "collection" );
4968  } else if( obj.has_member( "distribution" ) ) {
4969  gptr = std::make_unique<Item_group>( Item_group::G_DISTRIBUTION, probability, ig.with_ammo,
4970  ig.with_magazine, context, event );
4971  jarr = obj.get_array( "distribution" );
4972  }
4973  if( gptr ) {
4974  for( const JsonObject job2 : jarr ) {
4975  add_entry( *gptr, job2, subcontext );
4976  }
4977  ig.add_entry( std::move( gptr ) );
4978  return;
4979  }
4980 
4981  std::unique_ptr<Single_item_creator> sptr;
4982  if( obj.has_member( "item" ) ) {
4983  sptr = std::make_unique<Single_item_creator>(
4984  obj.get_string( "item" ), Single_item_creator::S_ITEM, probability, context, event );
4985  } else if( obj.has_member( "group" ) ) {
4986  sptr = std::make_unique<Single_item_creator>(
4987  obj.get_string( "group" ), Single_item_creator::S_ITEM_GROUP, probability,
4988  context, event );
4989  }
4990  if( !sptr ) {
4991  return;
4992  }
4993 
4994  if( obj.has_member( "artifact" ) ) {
4995  sptr->artifact = cata::make_value<Item_spawn_data::relic_generator>();
4996  sptr->artifact->load( obj.get_object( "artifact" ) );
4997  }
4998 
4999  Item_modifier modifier;
5000  bool use_modifier = false;
5001  use_modifier |= load_min_max( modifier.damage, obj, "damage" );
5002  use_modifier |= load_min_max( modifier.dirt, obj, "dirt" );
5003  modifier.damage.first *= itype::damage_scale;
5004  modifier.damage.second *= itype::damage_scale;
5005  use_modifier |= load_min_max( modifier.charges, obj, "charges" );
5006  use_modifier |= load_min_max( modifier.count, obj, "count" );
5007  use_modifier |= load_sub_ref( modifier.ammo, obj, "ammo", ig );
5008  if( obj.has_string( "entry-wrapper" ) ) {
5009  sptr->container_item = itype_id( obj.get_string( "entry-wrapper" ) );
5010  }
5011  if( obj.has_object( "container-item" ) ) {
5012  JsonObject jo = obj.get_object( "container-item" );
5013  sptr->container_item = itype_id( jo.get_string( "item" ) );
5014  sptr->container_item_variant = jo.get_string( "variant" );
5015  } else {
5016  use_modifier |= load_sub_ref( modifier.container, obj, "container", ig );
5017  }
5018  if( obj.has_array( "components" ) ) {
5019  JsonArray ja = obj.get_array( "components" );
5020  std::vector<itype_id> made_of;
5021  for( JsonValue sub : ja ) {
5022  itype_id component = itype_id( sub );
5023  made_of.emplace_back( component );
5024  }
5025  sptr->components_items = made_of;
5026  }
5027  use_modifier |= load_sub_ref( modifier.contents, obj, "contents", ig );
5028  use_modifier |= load_str_arr( modifier.snippets, obj, "snippets" );
5029  if( obj.has_member( "sealed" ) ) {
5030  modifier.sealed = obj.get_bool( "sealed" );
5031  use_modifier = true;
5032  }
5033  std::vector<std::string> custom_flags;
5034  use_modifier |= load_string( custom_flags, obj, "custom-flags" );
5035  modifier.custom_flags.clear();
5036  for( const auto &cf : custom_flags ) {
5037  modifier.custom_flags.emplace_back( cf );
5038  }
5039  if( obj.has_member( "variant" ) ) {
5040  modifier.variant = obj.get_string( "variant" );
5041  use_modifier = true;
5042  }
5043 
5044  if( use_modifier ) {
5045  sptr->modifier.emplace( std::move( modifier ) );
5046  }
5047  ig.add_entry( std::move( sptr ) );
5048 }

5058 void Item_factory::load_item_group( const JsonArray &entries, const item_group_id &group_id,
5059  const bool is_collection, const int ammo_chance,
5060  const int magazine_chance, std::string context )
5061 {
5062  if( context.empty() ) {
5063  context = group_id.str();
5064  }
5065  const Item_group::Type type = is_collection ? Item_group::G_COLLECTION : Item_group::G_DISTRIBUTION;
5066  std::unique_ptr<Item_spawn_data> &isd = m_template_groups[group_id];
5067  Item_group *const ig =
5068  make_group_or_throw( group_id, isd, type, ammo_chance, magazine_chance, context );
5069 
5070  for( const JsonObject subobj : entries ) {
5071  add_entry( *ig, subobj, "entry within " + ig->context() );
5072  }

5074 
5075 void Item_factory::load_item_group( const JsonObject &jsobj, const item_group_id &group_id,
5076  const std::string &subtype, std::string context )
5077 {
5078  if( context.empty() ) {
5079  context = group_id.str();
5080  }
5081  std::unique_ptr<Item_spawn_data> &isd = m_template_groups[group_id];
5082  // If we copy-from, do copy-from
5083  // Otherwise, unconditionally overwrite
5084  if( jsobj.has_member( "copy-from" ) ) {
5085  // We can only copy-from a group with the same id (for now)
5086  if( jsobj.get_string( "copy-from" ) != group_id.str() ) {
5087  debugmsg( "Item group '%s' tries to copy from different group '%s'", group_id.str(),
5088  jsobj.get_string( "copy-from" ) );
5089  return;
5090  }
5091  } else {
5092  isd.reset();
5093  }
5094 
5095  Item_group::Type type = Item_group::G_COLLECTION;
5096  if( subtype == "old" || subtype == "distribution" ) {
5097  type = Item_group::G_DISTRIBUTION;
5098  } else if( subtype != "collection" ) {
5099  jsobj.throw_error_at( "subtype", "unknown item group type" );
5100  }
5101  Item_group *ig = make_group_or_throw( group_id, isd, type, jsobj.get_int( "ammo", 0 ),
5102  jsobj.get_int( "magazine", 0 ), context );
5103 
5104  // If it extends, read from the extends block (and extend our itemgroup)
5105  // Otherwise, read from the object into the fresh itemgroup
5106  // And don't read if it has copy-from because it will not handle that correctly.
5107  if( jsobj.has_member( "extend" ) ) {
5108  load_item_group_data( jsobj.get_object( "extend" ), ig, subtype );
5109  } else if( !jsobj.has_member( "copy-from" ) ) {
5110  load_item_group_data( jsobj, ig, subtype );
5111  }
5112 
5113  if( jsobj.has_string( "container-item" ) ) {
5114  ig->container_item = itype_id( jsobj.get_string( "container-item" ) );
5115  } else if( jsobj.has_member( "container-item" ) ) {
5116  JsonObject jo = jsobj.get_member( "container-item" );
5117  ig->container_item = itype_id( jo.get_string( "item" ) );
5118  ig->container_item_variant = jo.get_string( "variant" );
5119  }
5120 
5121  jsobj.read( "on_overflow", ig->on_overflow, false );
5122  if( jsobj.has_member( "sealed" ) ) {
5123  ig->sealed = jsobj.get_bool( "sealed" );
5124  }
5125 }
5126 
5127 void Item_factory::load_item_group_data( const JsonObject &jsobj, Item_group *ig,
5128  const std::string &subtype )
5129 {
5130  if( subtype == "old" ) {
5131  for( const JsonValue entry : jsobj.get_array( "items" ) ) {
5132  if( entry.test_object() ) {
5133  JsonObject subobj = entry.get_object();
5134  std::string subcontext;
5135  if( subobj.has_string( "item" ) ) {
5136  subcontext = "item " + subobj.get_string( "item" ) + " within " + ig->context();
5137  } else if( subobj.has_string( "group" ) ) {
5138  subcontext = "group " + subobj.get_string( "group" ) + " within " + ig->context();
5139  } else if( subobj.has_member( "distribution" ) ) {
5140  subcontext = "distribution within " + ig->context();
5141  } else if( subobj.has_member( "collection" ) ) {
5142  subcontext = "collection within " + ig->context();
5143  } else {
5144  debugmsg( "couldn't determine subcontext for " + subobj.str() );
5145  subcontext = "item within " + ig->context();
5146  }
5147  add_entry( *ig, subobj, subcontext );
5148  } else {
5149  JsonArray pair = entry.get_array();
5150  ig->add_item_entry( itype_id( pair.get_string( 0 ) ), pair.get_int( 1 ) );
5151  }
5152  }
5153  return;
5154  }
5155 
5156  if( jsobj.has_member( "entries" ) ) {
5157  for( const JsonObject subobj : jsobj.get_array( "entries" ) ) {
5158  add_entry( *ig, subobj, "entry within " + ig->context() );
5159  }
5160  }
5161  if( jsobj.has_member( "items" ) ) {
5162  for( const JsonValue entry : jsobj.get_array( "items" ) ) {
5163  if( entry.test_string() ) {
5164  ig->add_item_entry( itype_id( entry.get_string() ), 100 );
5165  } else if( entry.test_array() ) {
5166  JsonArray subitem = entry.get_array();
5167  ig->add_item_entry( itype_id( subitem.get_string( 0 ) ), subitem.get_int( 1 ) );
5168  } else {
5169  JsonObject subobj = entry.get_object();
5170  add_entry( *ig, subobj, "item within " + ig->context() );
5171  }
5172  }
5173  }
5174  if( jsobj.has_member( "groups" ) ) {
5175  for( const JsonValue entry : jsobj.get_array( "groups" ) ) {
5176  if( entry.test_string() ) {
5177  ig->add_group_entry( item_group_id( entry.get_string() ), 100 );
5178  } else if( entry.test_array() ) {
5179  JsonArray subitem = entry.get_array();
5180  ig->add_group_entry( item_group_id( subitem.get_string( 0 ) ),
5181  subitem.get_int( 1 ) );
5182  } else {
5183  JsonObject subobj = entry.get_object();
5184  add_entry( *ig, subobj, "group within " + ig->context() );
5185  }
5186  }
5187  }
5188 }
5189 
5190 void Item_factory::set_use_methods_from_json( const JsonObject &jo, const std::string &member,
5191  std::map<std::string, use_function> &use_methods, std::map<std::string, int> &ammo_scale )
5192 {
5193  if( !jo.has_member( member ) ) {
5194  return;
5195  }
5196 
5197  use_methods.clear();
5198  ammo_scale.clear();
5199  if( jo.has_array( member ) ) {
5200  for( const JsonValue entry : jo.get_array( member ) ) {
5201  if( entry.test_string() ) {
5202  std::string type = entry.get_string();
5203  emplace_usage( use_methods, type );
5204  } else if( entry.test_object() ) {
5205  JsonObject obj = entry.get_object();
5206  std::pair<std::string, use_function> fun = usage_from_object( obj );
5207  if( fun.second ) {
5208  use_methods.insert( fun );
5209  if( obj.has_int( "ammo_scale" ) ) {
5210  ammo_scale.emplace( fun.first, static_cast<int>( obj.get_float( "ammo_scale" ) ) );
5211  }
5212  }
5213  } else if( entry.test_array() ) {
5214  JsonArray curr = entry.get_array();
5215  std::string type = curr.get_string( 0 );
5216  emplace_usage( use_methods, type );
5217  if( curr.has_int( 1 ) ) {
5218  ammo_scale.emplace( type, static_cast<int>( curr.get_float( 1 ) ) );
5219  }
5220  } else {
5221  entry.throw_error( "array element is neither string nor object." );
5222  }
5223  }
5224  } else {
5225  if( jo.has_string( member ) ) {
5226  std::string type = jo.get_string( member );
5227  emplace_usage( use_methods, type );
5228  } else if( jo.has_object( member ) ) {
5229  JsonObject obj = jo.get_object( member );
5230  std::pair<std::string, use_function> fun = usage_from_object( obj );
5231  if( fun.second ) {
5232  use_methods.insert( fun );
5233  if( obj.has_int( "ammo_scale" ) ) {
5234  ammo_scale.emplace( fun.first, static_cast<int>( obj.get_float( "ammo_scale" ) ) );
5235  }
5236  }
5237  } else {
5238  jo.throw_error( "member 'use_action' is neither string nor object." );
5239  }
5240 
5241  }
5242 }

5244 // Helper to safely look up and store iuse actions.
5245 void Item_factory::emplace_usage( std::map<std::string, use_function> &container,
5246  const std::string &iuse_id )
5247 {
5248  use_function fun = usage_from_string( iuse_id );
5249  if( fun ) {
5250  container.emplace( iuse_id, fun );
5251  }
5252 }

5254 std::pair<std::string, use_function> Item_factory::usage_from_object( const JsonObject &obj )
5255 {
5256  std::string type = obj.get_string( "type" );
5257 
5258  if( type == "repair_item" ) {
5259  type = obj.get_string( "item_action_type" );
5260  if( !has_iuse( type ) ) {
5261  add_actor( std::make_unique<repair_item_actor>( type ) );
5262  repair_actions.insert( type );
5263  }
5264  }
5265 
5266  use_function method = usage_from_string( type );
5267 
5268  if( !method.get_actor_ptr() ) {
5269  return std::make_pair( type, use_function() );
5270  }
5271 
5272  method.get_actor_ptr()->load( obj );
5273  return std::make_pair( type, method );
5274 }
5275 
5276 use_function Item_factory::usage_from_string( const std::string &type ) const
5277 {
5278  auto func = iuse_function_list.find( type );
5279  if( func != iuse_function_list.end() ) {
5280  return func->second;
5281  }
5282 
5283  // Otherwise, return a hardcoded function we know exists (hopefully)
5284  debugmsg( "Received unrecognized iuse function %s, using iuse::none instead", type.c_str() );
5285  return use_function();
5286 }
